v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

43// For WebAssembly we care about the full floating point (Simd) registers. If we
44// are not running Wasm, we can get away with saving half of those (F64)
45// registers.
46#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
47constexpr int kStackSavedSavedFPSizeInBytes =
48 kNumCallerSavedDoubles * kSimd128Size;
49#else
50constexpr int kStackSavedSavedFPSizeInBytes =
51 kNumCallerSavedDoubles * kDoubleSize;
52#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
53
54} // namespace

56void MacroAssembler::DoubleMax(DoubleRegister result_reg,
57 DoubleRegister left_reg,
58 DoubleRegister right_reg) {
59 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(VECTOR_ENHANCE_FACILITY_1)) {
60 vfmax(result_reg, left_reg, right_reg, Condition(1), Condition(8),
61 Condition(3));
62 return;
63 }
64
65 Label check_zero, return_left, return_right, return_nan, done;
66 cdbr(left_reg, right_reg);
67 bunordered(&return_nan, Label::kNear);
68 beq(&check_zero);
69 bge(&return_left, Label::kNear);
70 b(&return_right, Label::kNear);
71
72 bind(&check_zero);
73 lzdr(kDoubleRegZero);
74 cdbr(left_reg, kDoubleRegZero);
75 /* left == right != 0. */
76 bne(&return_left, Label::kNear);
77 /* At this point, both left and right are either 0 or -0. */
78 /* N.B. The following works because +0 + -0 == +0 */
79 /* For max we want logical-and of sign bit: (L + R) */
80 ldr(result_reg, left_reg);
81 adbr(result_reg, right_reg);
82 b(&done, Label::kNear);
83
84 bind(&return_nan);
85 /* If left or right are NaN, adbr propagates the appropriate one.*/
86 adbr(left_reg, right_reg);
87 b(&return_left, Label::kNear);
88
89 bind(&return_right);
90 if (right_reg != result_reg) {
91 ldr(result_reg, right_reg);
92 }
93 b(&done, Label::kNear);
94
95 bind(&return_left);
96 if (left_reg != result_reg) {
97 ldr(result_reg, left_reg);
98 }
99 bind(&done);
100}
101
102void MacroAssembler::DoubleMin(DoubleRegister result_reg,
103 DoubleRegister left_reg,
104 DoubleRegister right_reg) {
105 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(VECTOR_ENHANCE_FACILITY_1)) {
106 vfmin(result_reg, left_reg, right_reg, Condition(1), Condition(8),
107 Condition(3));
108 return;
109 }
110 Label check_zero, return_left, return_right, return_nan, done;
111 cdbr(left_reg, right_reg);
112 bunordered(&return_nan, Label::kNear);
113 beq(&check_zero);
114 ble(&return_left, Label::kNear);
115 b(&return_right, Label::kNear);
116
117 bind(&check_zero);
118 lzdr(kDoubleRegZero);
119 cdbr(left_reg, kDoubleRegZero);
120 /* left == right != 0. */
121 bne(&return_left, Label::kNear);
122 /* At this point, both left and right are either 0 or -0. */
123 /* N.B. The following works because +0 + -0 == +0 */
124 /* For min we want logical-or of sign bit: -(-L + -R) */
125 lcdbr(left_reg, left_reg);
126 ldr(result_reg, left_reg);
127 if (left_reg == right_reg) {
128 adbr(result_reg, right_reg);
129 } else {
130 sdbr(result_reg, right_reg);
131 }
132 lcdbr(result_reg, result_reg);
133 b(&done, Label::kNear);
134
135 bind(&return_nan);
136 /* If left or right are NaN, adbr propagates the appropriate one.*/
137 adbr(left_reg, right_reg);
138 b(&return_left, Label::kNear);
139
140 bind(&return_right);
141 if (right_reg != result_reg) {
142 ldr(result_reg, right_reg);
143 }
144 b(&done, Label::kNear);
145
146 bind(&return_left);
147 if (left_reg != result_reg) {
148 ldr(result_reg, left_reg);
149 }
150 bind(&done);
151}

153void MacroAssembler::FloatMax(DoubleRegister result_reg,
154 DoubleRegister left_reg,
155 DoubleRegister right_reg) {
156 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(VECTOR_ENHANCE_FACILITY_1)) {
157 vfmax(result_reg, left_reg, right_reg, Condition(1), Condition(8),
158 Condition(2));
159 return;
160 }
161 Label check_zero, return_left, return_right, return_nan, done;
162 cebr(left_reg, right_reg);
163 bunordered(&return_nan, Label::kNear);
164 beq(&check_zero);
165 bge(&return_left, Label::kNear);
166 b(&return_right, Label::kNear);
167
168 bind(&check_zero);
169 lzdr(kDoubleRegZero);
170 cebr(left_reg, kDoubleRegZero);
171 /* left == right != 0. */
172 bne(&return_left, Label::kNear);
173 /* At this point, both left and right are either 0 or -0. */
174 /* N.B. The following works because +0 + -0 == +0 */
175 /* For max we want logical-and of sign bit: (L + R) */
176 ldr(result_reg, left_reg);
177 aebr(result_reg, right_reg);
178 b(&done, Label::kNear);
179
180 bind(&return_nan);
181 /* If left or right are NaN, aebr propagates the appropriate one.*/
182 aebr(left_reg, right_reg);
183 b(&return_left, Label::kNear);
184
185 bind(&return_right);
186 if (right_reg != result_reg) {
187 ldr(result_reg, right_reg);
188 }
189 b(&done, Label::kNear);
190
191 bind(&return_left);
192 if (left_reg != result_reg) {
193 ldr(result_reg, left_reg);
194 }
195 bind(&done);
196}

198void MacroAssembler::FloatMin(DoubleRegister result_reg,
199 DoubleRegister left_reg,
200 DoubleRegister right_reg) {
201 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(VECTOR_ENHANCE_FACILITY_1)) {
202 vfmin(result_reg, left_reg, right_reg, Condition(1), Condition(8),
203 Condition(2));
204 return;
205 }
206
207 Label check_zero, return_left, return_right, return_nan, done;
208 cebr(left_reg, right_reg);
209 bunordered(&return_nan, Label::kNear);
210 beq(&check_zero);
211 ble(&return_left, Label::kNear);
212 b(&return_right, Label::kNear);
213
214 bind(&check_zero);
215 lzdr(kDoubleRegZero);
216 cebr(left_reg, kDoubleRegZero);
217 /* left == right != 0. */
218 bne(&return_left, Label::kNear);
219 /* At this point, both left and right are either 0 or -0. */
220 /* N.B. The following works because +0 + -0 == +0 */
221 /* For min we want logical-or of sign bit: -(-L + -R) */
222 lcebr(left_reg, left_reg);
223 ldr(result_reg, left_reg);
224 if (left_reg == right_reg) {
225 aebr(result_reg, right_reg);
226 } else {
227 sebr(result_reg, right_reg);
228 }
229 lcebr(result_reg, result_reg);
230 b(&done, Label::kNear);
231
232 bind(&return_nan);
233 /* If left or right are NaN, aebr propagates the appropriate one.*/
234 aebr(left_reg, right_reg);
235 b(&return_left, Label::kNear);
236
237 bind(&return_right);
238 if (right_reg != result_reg) {
239 ldr(result_reg, right_reg);
240 }
241 b(&done, Label::kNear);
242
243 bind(&return_left);
244 if (left_reg != result_reg) {
245 ldr(result_reg, left_reg);
246 }
247 bind(&done);
248}

282int MacroAssembler::RequiredStackSizeForCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
283 Register exclusion1,
284 Register exclusion2,
285 Register exclusion3) const {
286 int bytes = 0;
287
288 RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
289 RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
290 bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
291
292 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
293 bytes += kStackSavedSavedFPSizeInBytes;
294 }
295
296 return bytes;
297}
298
299int MacroAssembler::PushCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, Register scratch,
300 Register exclusion1, Register exclusion2,
301 Register exclusion3) {
302 int bytes = 0;
303
304 RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
305 RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
306 MultiPush(list);
307 bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
308
309 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
310 MultiPushF64OrV128(kCallerSavedDoubles, scratch);
311 bytes += kStackSavedSavedFPSizeInBytes;
312 }
313
314 return bytes;
315}
316
317int MacroAssembler::PopCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, Register scratch,
318 Register exclusion1, Register exclusion2,
319 Register exclusion3) {
320 int bytes = 0;
321 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
322 MultiPopF64OrV128(kCallerSavedDoubles, scratch);
323 bytes += kStackSavedSavedFPSizeInBytes;
324 }
325
326 RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
327 RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
328 MultiPop(list);
329 bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
330
331 return bytes;
332}

334void MacroAssembler::LoadFromConstantsTable(Register destination,
335 int constant_index) {
336 DCHECK(RootsTable::IsImmortalImmovable(RootIndex::kBuiltinsConstantsTable));
337
338 const uint32_t offset = OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) +
339 constant_index * kSystemPointerSize - kHeapObjectTag;
340
341 CHECK(is_uint19(offset));
342 DCHECK_NE(destination, r0);
343 LoadRoot(destination, RootIndex::kBuiltinsConstantsTable);
344 LoadTaggedField(destination,
345 FieldMemOperand(destination, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(
346 constant_index)),
347 r1);
348}

350void MacroAssembler::LoadRootRelative(Register destination, int32_t offset) {
351 LoadU64(destination, MemOperand(kRootRegister, offset));
352}
353
354void MacroAssembler::StoreRootRelative(int32_t offset, Register value) {
355 StoreU64(value, MemOperand(kRootRegister, offset));
356}
357
358void MacroAssembler::LoadRootRegisterOffset(Register destination,
359 intptr_t offset) {
360 if (offset == 0) {
361 mov(destination, kRootRegister);
362 } else if (is_uint12(offset)) {
363 la(destination, MemOperand(kRootRegister, offset));
364 } else {
365 DCHECK(is_int20(offset));
366 lay(destination, MemOperand(kRootRegister, offset));
367 }
368}
369
370MemOperand MacroAssembler::ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
371 ExternalReference reference, Register scratch) {
372 if (root_array_available()) {
373 if (reference.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
374 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, reference.offset_from_root_register());
375 }
376 if (options().enable_root_relative_access) {
377 intptr_t offset =
378 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
379 if (is_int32(offset)) {
380 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
381 }
382 }
383 if (options().isolate_independent_code) {
384 if (IsAddressableThroughRootRegister(isolate(), reference)) {
385 // Some external references can be efficiently loaded as an offset from
386 // kRootRegister.
387 intptr_t offset =
388 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
389 CHECK(is_int32(offset));
390 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
391 } else {
392 // Otherwise, do a memory load from the external reference table.
393 LoadU64(scratch,
394 MemOperand(kRootRegister,
395 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReferenceTableEntry(
396 isolate(), reference)));
397 return MemOperand(scratch, 0);
398 }
399 }
400 }
401 Move(scratch, reference);
402 return MemOperand(scratch, 0);
403}

405void MacroAssembler::Jump(Register target, Condition cond) { b(cond, target); }
406
407void MacroAssembler::Jump(intptr_t target, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
408 Condition cond) {
409 Label skip;
410
411 if (cond != al) b(NegateCondition(cond), &skip);
412
413 mov(ip, Operand(target, rmode));
414 b(ip);
415
416 bind(&skip);
417}
418
419void MacroAssembler::Jump(Address target, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
420 Condition cond) {
421 DCHECK(!RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
422 Jump(static_cast<intptr_t>(target), rmode, cond);
423}
424
425void MacroAssembler::Jump(Handle<Code> code, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
426 Condition cond) {
427 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
428 DCHECK_IMPLIES(options().isolate_independent_code,
429 Builtins::IsIsolateIndependentBuiltin(*code));
430
431 Builtin builtin = Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
432 if (isolate()->builtins()->IsBuiltinHandle(code, &builtin)) {
433 TailCallBuiltin(builtin, cond);
434 return;
435 }
436 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
437 jump(code, RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET, cond);
438}
439
440void MacroAssembler::Jump(const ExternalReference& reference) {
441#if V8_OS_ZOS
442 // Place reference into scratch r12 ip register
443 Move(ip, reference);
444 // z/OS uses function descriptors, extract code entry into r6
445 LoadMultipleP(r5, r6, MemOperand(ip));
446 // Preserve return address into r14
447 mov(r14, r7);
448 // Call C Function
449 StoreReturnAddressAndCall(r6);
450 // Branch to return address in r14
451 b(r14);
452#else
453 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
454 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
455 Move(scratch, reference);
456 Jump(scratch);
457#endif
458}

460void MacroAssembler::Call(Register target) {
461 // Branch to target via indirect branch
462 basr(r14, target);
463}
464
465void MacroAssembler::CallJSEntry(Register target) {
466 DCHECK(target == r4);
467 Call(target);
468}

470int MacroAssembler::CallSizeNotPredictableCodeSize(Address target,
471 RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
472 Condition cond) {
473 // S390 Assembler::move sequence is IILF / IIHF
474 int size;
475 size = 14; // IILF + IIHF + BASR
476 return size;
477}

479void MacroAssembler::Call(Address target, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
480 Condition cond) {
481 DCHECK(cond == al);
482
483 mov(ip, Operand(target, rmode));
484 basr(r14, ip);
485}
486
487void MacroAssembler::Call(Handle<Code> code, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
488 Condition cond) {
489 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode) && cond == al);
490
491 DCHECK_IMPLIES(options().isolate_independent_code,
492 Builtins::IsIsolateIndependentBuiltin(*code));
493
494 Builtin builtin = Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
495 if (isolate()->builtins()->IsBuiltinHandle(code, &builtin)) {
496 CallBuiltin(builtin);
497 return;
498 }
499 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
500 call(code, rmode);
501}
502
503void MacroAssembler::CallBuiltin(Builtin builtin, Condition cond) {
504 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("call", builtin));
505 // Use ip directly instead of using UseScratchRegisterScope, as we do not
506 // preserve scratch registers across calls.
507 switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
508 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute: {
509 mov(ip, Operand(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET));
510 Call(ip);
511 break;
512 }
513 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
514 UNREACHABLE();
515 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect:
516 LoadU64(ip, EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(builtin));
517 Call(ip);
518 break;
519 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
520 Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
521 call(code, RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
522 break;
523 }
524 }
525}
526
527void MacroAssembler::TailCallBuiltin(Builtin builtin, Condition cond) {
528 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this,
529 CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("tail call", builtin));
530 // Use ip directly instead of using UseScratchRegisterScope, as we do not
531 // preserve scratch registers across calls.
532 switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
533 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute: {
534 mov(ip, Operand(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET));
535 Jump(ip, cond);
536 break;
537 }
538 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
539 UNREACHABLE();
540 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect:
541 LoadU64(ip, EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(builtin));
542 Jump(ip, cond);
543 break;
544 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
545 if (options().use_pc_relative_calls_and_jumps_for_mksnapshot) {
546 Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
547 jump(code, RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET, cond);
548 } else {
549 LoadU64(ip, EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(builtin));
550 Jump(ip, cond);
551 }
552 break;
553 }
554 }
555}
556
557void MacroAssembler::Drop(int count) {
558 if (count > 0) {
559 int total = count * kSystemPointerSize;
560 if (is_uint12(total)) {
561 la(sp, MemOperand(sp, total));
562 } else if (is_int20(total)) {
563 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, total));
564 } else {
565 AddS64(sp, Operand(total));
566 }
567 }
568}
569
570void MacroAssembler::Drop(Register count, Register scratch) {
571 ShiftLeftU64(scratch, count, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
572 AddS64(sp, sp, scratch);
573}

575void MacroAssembler::TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(Register code,
576 Register scratch) {
577 LoadU32(scratch, FieldMemOperand(code, Code::kFlagsOffset));
578 TestBit(scratch, Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit, scratch);
579}

597void MacroAssembler::Push(Tagged<TaggedIndex> index) {
598 // TaggedIndex is the same as Smi for 32 bit archs.

602
603void MacroAssembler::Move(Register dst, Handle<HeapObject> value,
604 RelocInfo::Mode rmode) {
605 // TODO(jgruber,v8:8887): Also consider a root-relative load when generating
606 // non-isolate-independent code. In many cases it might be cheaper than
607 // embedding the relocatable value.
608 if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {
609 IndirectLoadConstant(dst, value);
610 return;
611 } else if (RelocInfo::IsCompressedEmbeddedObject(rmode)) {
612 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(value);
613 DCHECK(is_uint32(index));
614 mov(dst, Operand(static_cast<int>(index), rmode));
615 } else {
616 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsFullEmbeddedObject(rmode));
617 mov(dst, Operand(value.address(), rmode));
618 }
619}
620
621void MacroAssembler::Move(Register dst, ExternalReference reference) {
622 if (root_array_available()) {
623 if (reference.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
624 AddS64(dst, kRootRegister,
625 Operand(reference.offset_from_root_register()));
626 return;
627 }
628 if (options().isolate_independent_code) {
629 IndirectLoadExternalReference(dst, reference);
630 return;
631 }
632 }
633
634 // External references should not get created with IDs if
635 // `!root_array_available()`.
636 CHECK(!reference.IsIsolateFieldId());
637 mov(dst, Operand(reference));
638}
639
640void MacroAssembler::LoadIsolateField(Register dst, IsolateFieldId id) {
641 Move(dst, ExternalReference::Create(id));
642}
643
644void MacroAssembler::Move(Register dst, Register src, Condition cond) {
645 if (dst != src) {
646 if (cond == al) {
647 mov(dst, src);
648 } else {
649 LoadOnConditionP(cond, dst, src);
650 }
651 }
652}
653
654void MacroAssembler::Move(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister src) {
655 if (dst != src) {
656 ldr(dst, src);
657 }
658}
659
660void MacroAssembler::Move(Register dst, const MemOperand& src) {
661 LoadU64(dst, src);
662}

664// Wrapper around Assembler::mvc (SS-a format)
665void MacroAssembler::MoveChar(const MemOperand& opnd1, const MemOperand& opnd2,
666 const Operand& length) {
667 mvc(opnd1, opnd2, Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(length.immediate() - 1)));
668}

670// Wrapper around Assembler::clc (SS-a format)
671void MacroAssembler::CompareLogicalChar(const MemOperand& opnd1,
672 const MemOperand& opnd2,
673 const Operand& length) {
674 clc(opnd1, opnd2, Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(length.immediate() - 1)));

676
677// Wrapper around Assembler::xc (SS-a format)
678void MacroAssembler::ExclusiveOrChar(const MemOperand& opnd1,
679 const MemOperand& opnd2,
680 const Operand& length) {
681 xc(opnd1, opnd2, Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(length.immediate() - 1)));
682}
683
684// Wrapper around Assembler::risbg(n) (RIE-f)
685void MacroAssembler::RotateInsertSelectBits(Register dst, Register src,
686 const Operand& startBit,
687 const Operand& endBit,
688 const Operand& shiftAmt,
689 bool zeroBits) {
690 if (zeroBits)
691 // High tag the top bit of I4/EndBit to zero out any unselected bits
692 risbg(dst, src, startBit,
693 Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(endBit.immediate() | 0x80)), shiftAmt);
694 else
695 risbg(dst, src, startBit, endBit, shiftAmt);
696}
697
698void MacroAssembler::BranchRelativeOnIdxHighP(Register dst, Register inc,
699 Label* L) {
700 brxhg(dst, inc, L);
701}
702
703void MacroAssembler::PushArray(Register array, Register size, Register scratch,
704 Register scratch2, PushArrayOrder order) {
705 Label loop, done;
706
707 if (order == kNormal) {
708 ShiftLeftU64(scratch, size, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
709 lay(scratch, MemOperand(array, scratch));
710 bind(&loop);
711 CmpS64(array, scratch);
712 bge(&done);
713 lay(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, -kSystemPointerSize));
714 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kSystemPointerSize));
715 MoveChar(MemOperand(sp), MemOperand(scratch), Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
716 b(&loop);
717 bind(&done);
718 } else {
719 DCHECK_NE(scratch2, r0);
720 ShiftLeftU64(scratch, size, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
721 lay(scratch, MemOperand(array, scratch));
722 mov(scratch2, array);
723 bind(&loop);
724 CmpS64(scratch2, scratch);
725 bge(&done);
726 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kSystemPointerSize));
727 MoveChar(MemOperand(sp), MemOperand(scratch2), Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
728 lay(scratch2, MemOperand(scratch2, kSystemPointerSize));
729 b(&loop);
730 bind(&done);
731 }
732}
733
734void MacroAssembler::MultiPush(RegList regs, Register location) {
735 int16_t num_to_push = regs.Count();
736 int16_t stack_offset = num_to_push * kSystemPointerSize;
737
738 SubS64(location, location, Operand(stack_offset));
739 for (int16_t i = Register::kNumRegisters - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
740 if ((regs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
741 stack_offset -= kSystemPointerSize;
742 StoreU64(ToRegister(i), MemOperand(location, stack_offset));
743 }
744 }
745}
746
747void MacroAssembler::MultiPop(RegList regs, Register location) {
748 int16_t stack_offset = 0;
749
750 for (int16_t i = 0; i < Register::kNumRegisters; i++) {
751 if ((regs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
752 LoadU64(ToRegister(i), MemOperand(location, stack_offset));
753 stack_offset += kSystemPointerSize;
754 }
755 }
756 AddS64(location, location, Operand(stack_offset));
757}
758
759void MacroAssembler::MultiPushDoubles(DoubleRegList dregs, Register location) {
760 int16_t num_to_push = dregs.Count();
761 int16_t stack_offset = num_to_push * kDoubleSize;
762
763 SubS64(location, location, Operand(stack_offset));
764 for (int16_t i = DoubleRegister::kNumRegisters - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
765 if ((dregs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
766 DoubleRegister dreg = DoubleRegister::from_code(i);
767 stack_offset -= kDoubleSize;
768 StoreF64(dreg, MemOperand(location, stack_offset));
769 }
770 }
771}
772
773void MacroAssembler::MultiPushV128(DoubleRegList dregs, Register scratch,
774 Register location) {
775 int16_t num_to_push = dregs.Count();
776 int16_t stack_offset = num_to_push * kSimd128Size;
777
778 SubS64(location, location, Operand(stack_offset));
779 for (int16_t i = Simd128Register::kNumRegisters - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
780 if ((dregs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
781 Simd128Register dreg = Simd128Register::from_code(i);
782 stack_offset -= kSimd128Size;
783 StoreV128(dreg, MemOperand(location, stack_offset), scratch);
784 }
785 }
786}
787
788void MacroAssembler::MultiPopDoubles(DoubleRegList dregs, Register location) {
789 int16_t stack_offset = 0;
790
791 for (int16_t i = 0; i < DoubleRegister::kNumRegisters; i++) {
792 if ((dregs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
793 DoubleRegister dreg = DoubleRegister::from_code(i);
794 LoadF64(dreg, MemOperand(location, stack_offset));
795 stack_offset += kDoubleSize;
796 }
797 }
798 AddS64(location, location, Operand(stack_offset));
799}
800
801void MacroAssembler::MultiPopV128(DoubleRegList dregs, Register scratch,
802 Register location) {
803 int16_t stack_offset = 0;
804
805 for (int16_t i = 0; i < Simd128Register::kNumRegisters; i++) {
806 if ((dregs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
807 Simd128Register dreg = Simd128Register::from_code(i);
808 LoadV128(dreg, MemOperand(location, stack_offset), scratch);
809 stack_offset += kSimd128Size;
810 }
811 }
812 AddS64(location, location, Operand(stack_offset));
813}
814
815void MacroAssembler::MultiPushF64OrV128(DoubleRegList dregs, Register scratch,
816 Register location) {
817#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
818 bool generating_bultins =
819 isolate() && isolate()->IsGeneratingEmbeddedBuiltins();
820 if (generating_bultins) {
821 Label push_doubles, simd_pushed;
822 Move(r1, ExternalReference::supports_wasm_simd_128_address());
823 LoadU8(r1, MemOperand(r1));
824 LoadAndTestP(r1, r1); // If > 0 then simd is available.
825 ble(&push_doubles, Label::kNear);
826 // Save vector registers, don't save double registers anymore.
827 MultiPushV128(dregs, scratch);
828 b(&simd_pushed);
829 bind(&push_doubles);
830 // Simd not supported, only save double registers.
831 MultiPushDoubles(dregs);
832 // We still need to allocate empty space on the stack as if
833 // Simd rgeisters were saved (see kFixedFrameSizeFromFp).
834 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -(dregs.Count() * kDoubleSize)));
835 bind(&simd_pushed);
836 } else {
837 if (CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128()) {
838 MultiPushV128(dregs, scratch);
839 } else {
840 MultiPushDoubles(dregs);
841 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -(dregs.Count() * kDoubleSize)));
842 }
843 }
844#else
845 MultiPushDoubles(dregs);
846#endif
847}
848
849void MacroAssembler::MultiPopF64OrV128(DoubleRegList dregs, Register scratch,
850 Register location) {
851#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
852 bool generating_bultins =
853 isolate() && isolate()->IsGeneratingEmbeddedBuiltins();
854 if (generating_bultins) {
855 Label pop_doubles, simd_popped;
856 Move(r1, ExternalReference::supports_wasm_simd_128_address());
857 LoadU8(r1, MemOperand(r1));
858 LoadAndTestP(r1, r1); // If > 0 then simd is available.
859 ble(&pop_doubles, Label::kNear);
860 // Pop vector registers, don't pop double registers anymore.
861 MultiPopV128(dregs, scratch);
862 b(&simd_popped);
863 bind(&pop_doubles);
864 // Simd not supported, only pop double registers.
865 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, dregs.Count() * kDoubleSize));
866 MultiPopDoubles(dregs);
867 bind(&simd_popped);
868 } else {
869 if (CpuFeatures::SupportsWasmSimd128()) {
870 MultiPopV128(dregs, scratch);
871 } else {
872 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, dregs.Count() * kDoubleSize));
873 MultiPopDoubles(dregs);
874 }
875 }
876#else
877 MultiPopDoubles(dregs);
878#endif
879}
880
881void MacroAssembler::PushAll(RegList registers) {
882 if (registers.is_empty()) return;
883 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
884 // TODO(victorgomes): {stm/ldm} pushes/pops registers in the opposite order
885 // as expected by Maglev frame. Consider massaging Maglev to accept this
886 // order instead.
887 // Can not use MultiPush(registers, sp) due to orders
888 for (Register reg : registers) {
889 Push(reg);
890 }
891}
892
893void MacroAssembler::PopAll(RegList registers) {
894 if (registers.is_empty()) return;
895 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
896 // Can not use MultiPop(registers, sp);
897 for (Register reg : base::Reversed(registers)) {
898 Pop(reg);
899 }
900}
901
902void MacroAssembler::PushAll(DoubleRegList registers, int stack_slot_size) {
903 if (registers.is_empty()) return;
904 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
905 MultiPushDoubles(registers, sp);
906}
907
908void MacroAssembler::PopAll(DoubleRegList registers, int stack_slot_size) {
909 if (registers.is_empty()) return;
910 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
911 MultiPopDoubles(registers, sp);
912}

914void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index) {
915 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
916 if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
917 mov(destination, Operand(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index), RelocInfo::Mode::NO_INFO));
918 return;
919 }
920 LoadRoot(destination, index);
921}
922
923void MacroAssembler::LoadRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index,
924 Condition) {
925 if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
926 DecompressTagged(destination, ReadOnlyRootPtr(index));
927 return;
928 }
929 LoadU64(destination,
930 MemOperand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index)), r0);
931}

933void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedField(const Register& destination,
934 const MemOperand& field_operand,
935 const Register& scratch) {
936 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
937 DecompressTagged(destination, field_operand);
938 } else {
939 LoadU64(destination, field_operand, scratch);
940 }
941}
942void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedFieldWithoutDecompressing(
943 const Register& destination, const MemOperand& field_operand,
944 const Register& scratch) {
945 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
946 LoadU32(destination, field_operand, scratch);
947 } else {
948 LoadU64(destination, field_operand, scratch);
949 }
950}
951void MacroAssembler::SmiUntag(Register dst, const MemOperand& src) {
952 if (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
953 LoadS32(dst, src);
954 } else {
955 LoadU64(dst, src);
956 }
957 SmiUntag(dst);
958}
959
960void MacroAssembler::SmiUntagField(Register dst, const MemOperand& src) {
961 SmiUntag(dst, src);
962}
963
964void MacroAssembler::StoreTaggedField(const Register& value,
965 const MemOperand& dst_field_operand,
966 const Register& scratch) {
967 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
968 RecordComment("[ StoreTagged");
969 StoreU32(value, dst_field_operand);
970 RecordComment("]");
971 } else {
972 StoreU64(value, dst_field_operand, scratch);
973 }
974}

991 RecordComment("[ DecompressTagged");
992 llgfr(destination, source);
993 agr(destination, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister);
994 RecordComment("]");
995}

997void MacroAssembler::DecompressTagged(Register destination,
998 MemOperand field_operand) {
999 RecordComment("[ DecompressTagged");
1000 llgf(destination, field_operand);
1001 agr(destination, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister);
1002 RecordComment("]");
1003}

1005void MacroAssembler::DecompressTagged(const Register& destination,
1006 Tagged_t immediate) {
1007 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1008 mov(destination, Operand(immediate, RelocInfo::NO_INFO));
1009 agr(destination, kRootRegister);
1010}
1011
1012void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedSignedField(Register destination,
1013 MemOperand field_operand) {
1014 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1015 DecompressTaggedSigned(destination, field_operand);
1016 } else {
1017 LoadU64(destination, field_operand);
1018 }
1019}
1020
1021void MacroAssembler::RecordWriteField(Register object, int offset,
1022 Register value, Register slot_address,
1023 LinkRegisterStatus lr_status,
1024 SaveFPRegsMode save_fp,
1025 SmiCheck smi_check) {
1026 // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
1027 // catch stores of Smis.
1028 Label done;
1029
1030 // Skip barrier if writing a smi.
1031 if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
1032 JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
1033 }
1034
1035 // Although the object register is tagged, the offset is relative to the start
1036 // of the object, so so offset must be a multiple of kSystemPointerSize.
1037 DCHECK(IsAligned(offset, kTaggedSize));
1038
1039 lay(slot_address, MemOperand(object, offset - kHeapObjectTag));
1040 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
1041 Label ok;
1042 AndP(r0, slot_address, Operand(kTaggedSize - 1));
1043 beq(&ok, Label::kNear);
1044 stop();
1045 bind(&ok);
1046 }
1047
1048 RecordWrite(object, slot_address, value, lr_status, save_fp, SmiCheck::kOmit);
1049
1050 bind(&done);
1051
1052 // Clobber clobbered input registers when running with the debug-code flag
1053 // turned on to provoke errors.
1054 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
1055 mov(value, Operand(base::bit_cast<intptr_t>(kZapValue + 4)));
1056 mov(slot_address, Operand(base::bit_cast<intptr_t>(kZapValue + 8)));
1057 }
1058}
1059
1060void MacroAssembler::MaybeSaveRegisters(RegList registers) {
1061 if (registers.is_empty()) return;
1062 MultiPush(registers);
1063}
1064
1065void MacroAssembler::MaybeRestoreRegisters(RegList registers) {
1066 if (registers.is_empty()) return;
1067 MultiPop(registers);
1068}
1069
1070void MacroAssembler::CallEphemeronKeyBarrier(Register object,
1071 Register slot_address,
1072 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode) {
1073 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, slot_address));
1074 RegList registers =
1075 WriteBarrierDescriptor::ComputeSavedRegisters(object, slot_address);
1076 MaybeSaveRegisters(registers);
1077
1078 Register object_parameter = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
1079 Register slot_address_parameter =
1080 WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
1081
1082 Push(object);
1083 Push(slot_address);
1084 Pop(slot_address_parameter);
1085 Pop(object_parameter);
1086
1087 CallBuiltin(Builtins::EphemeronKeyBarrier(fp_mode));
1088 MaybeRestoreRegisters(registers);
1089}
1090
1091void MacroAssembler::CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(Register object,
1092 Register slot_address,
1093 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
1094 StubCallMode mode) {
1095 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, slot_address));
1096 RegList registers =
1097 WriteBarrierDescriptor::ComputeSavedRegisters(object, slot_address);
1098 MaybeSaveRegisters(registers);
1099
1100 Register object_parameter = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
1101 Register slot_address_parameter =
1102 WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
1103
1104 Push(object);
1105 Push(slot_address);
1106 Pop(slot_address_parameter);
1107 Pop(object_parameter);
1108
1109 CallRecordWriteStub(object_parameter, slot_address_parameter, fp_mode, mode);
1110
1111 MaybeRestoreRegisters(registers);
1112}
1113
1114void MacroAssembler::CallRecordWriteStub(Register object, Register slot_address,
1115 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
1116 StubCallMode mode) {
1117 // Use CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters if the object and slot registers
1118 // need to be caller saved.
1119 DCHECK_EQ(WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister(), object);
1120 DCHECK_EQ(WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister(), slot_address);
1121#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1122 if (mode == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
1123 auto wasm_target =
1124 static_cast<Address>(wasm::WasmCode::GetRecordWriteBuiltin(fp_mode));
1125 Call(wasm_target, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
1126#else
1127 if (false) {
1128#endif
1129 } else {
1130 CallBuiltin(Builtins::RecordWrite(fp_mode));
1131 }
1132}
1133
1134// Will clobber 4 registers: object, address, scratch, ip. The
1135// register 'object' contains a heap object pointer. The heap object
1136// tag is shifted away.
1137void MacroAssembler::RecordWrite(Register object, Register slot_address,
1138 Register value, LinkRegisterStatus lr_status,
1139 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, SmiCheck smi_check) {
1140 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, slot_address, value));
1141 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
1142 LoadTaggedField(r0, MemOperand(slot_address));
1143 CmpS64(value, r0);
1144 Check(eq, AbortReason::kWrongAddressOrValuePassedToRecordWrite);
1145 }
1146
1147 if (v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
1148 return;
1149 }
1150 // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
1151 // catch stores of smis and stores into the young generation.
1152 Label done;
1153
1154 if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
1155 JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
1156 }
1157
1158 CheckPageFlag(value,
1159 value, // Used as scratch.
1160 MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq, &done);
1161 CheckPageFlag(object,
1162 value, // Used as scratch.
1163 MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask, eq, &done);
1164
1165 // Record the actual write.
1166 if (lr_status == kLRHasNotBeenSaved) {
1167 push(r14);
1168 }
1169 CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(object, slot_address, fp_mode);
1170 if (lr_status == kLRHasNotBeenSaved) {
1171 pop(r14);
1172 }
1173
1174 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) mov(slot_address, Operand(kZapValue));
1175
1176 bind(&done);
1177
1178 // Clobber clobbered registers when running with the debug-code flag
1179 // turned on to provoke errors.
1180 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
1181 mov(slot_address, Operand(base::bit_cast<intptr_t>(kZapValue + 12)));
1182 mov(value, Operand(base::bit_cast<intptr_t>(kZapValue + 16)));
1183 }
1184}
1185
1186void MacroAssembler::PushCommonFrame(Register marker_reg) {
1187 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1188 int fp_delta = 0;
1189 if (marker_reg.is_valid()) {
1190 Push(r14, fp, marker_reg);
1191 fp_delta = 1;
1192 } else {
1193 Push(r14, fp);
1194 fp_delta = 0;
1195 }
1196 la(fp, MemOperand(sp, fp_delta * kSystemPointerSize));
1197}
1198
1199void MacroAssembler::PopCommonFrame(Register marker_reg) {
1200 if (marker_reg.is_valid()) {
1201 Pop(r14, fp, marker_reg);
1202 } else {
1203 Pop(r14, fp);
1204 }
1205}
1206
1207void MacroAssembler::PushStandardFrame(Register function_reg) {
1208 int fp_delta = 0;
1209 if (function_reg.is_valid()) {
1210 Push(r14, fp, cp, function_reg);
1211 fp_delta = 2;
1212 } else {
1213 Push(r14, fp, cp);
1214 fp_delta = 1;
1215 }
1216 la(fp, MemOperand(sp, fp_delta * kSystemPointerSize));
1217 Push(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
1218}
1219
1220void MacroAssembler::RestoreFrameStateForTailCall() {
1221 // if (V8_EMBEDDED_CONSTANT_POOL_BOOL) {
1222 // LoadU64(kConstantPoolRegister,
1223 // MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kConstantPoolOffset));
1224 // set_constant_pool_available(false);
1225 // }
1226 DCHECK(!V8_EMBEDDED_CONSTANT_POOL_BOOL);
1227 LoadU64(r14, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
1228 LoadU64(fp, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset));
1229}

1231void MacroAssembler::CanonicalizeNaN(const DoubleRegister dst,
1232 const DoubleRegister src) {
1233 // Turn potential sNaN into qNaN
1234 if (dst != src) ldr(dst, src);
1235 lzdr(kDoubleRegZero);
1236 sdbr(dst, kDoubleRegZero);
1237}

1239void MacroAssembler::ConvertIntToDouble(DoubleRegister dst, Register src) {
1240 cdfbr(dst, src);
1241}

1243void MacroAssembler::ConvertUnsignedIntToDouble(DoubleRegister dst,
1244 Register src) {
1245 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(FLOATING_POINT_EXT)) {
1246 cdlfbr(Condition(5), Condition(0), dst, src);
1247 } else {
1248 // zero-extend src
1249 llgfr(src, src);
1250 // convert to double
1251 cdgbr(dst, src);
1252 }
1253}

1283
1284void MacroAssembler::ConvertFloat32ToInt64(const Register dst,
1285 const DoubleRegister double_input,
1286 FPRoundingMode rounding_mode) {
1287 Condition m = Condition(0);
1288 switch (rounding_mode) {
1289 case kRoundToZero:
1290 m = Condition(5);
1291 break;
1292 case kRoundToNearest:
1293 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1294 case kRoundToPlusInf:
1295 m = Condition(6);
1296 break;
1297 case kRoundToMinusInf:
1298 m = Condition(7);
1299 break;
1300 default:
1301 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1302 }
1303 cgebr(m, dst, double_input);
1304}
1305
1306void MacroAssembler::ConvertDoubleToInt64(const Register dst,
1307 const DoubleRegister double_input,
1308 FPRoundingMode rounding_mode) {
1309 Condition m = Condition(0);
1310 switch (rounding_mode) {
1311 case kRoundToZero:
1312 m = Condition(5);
1313 break;
1314 case kRoundToNearest:
1315 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1316 case kRoundToPlusInf:
1317 m = Condition(6);
1318 break;
1319 case kRoundToMinusInf:
1320 m = Condition(7);
1321 break;
1322 default:
1323 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1324 }
1325 cgdbr(m, dst, double_input);
1326}
1327
1328void MacroAssembler::ConvertDoubleToInt32(const Register dst,
1329 const DoubleRegister double_input,
1330 FPRoundingMode rounding_mode) {
1331 Condition m = Condition(0);
1332 switch (rounding_mode) {
1333 case kRoundToZero:
1334 m = Condition(5);
1335 break;
1336 case kRoundToNearest:
1337 m = Condition(4);
1338 break;
1339 case kRoundToPlusInf:
1340 m = Condition(6);
1341 break;
1342 case kRoundToMinusInf:
1343 m = Condition(7);
1344 break;
1345 default:
1346 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1347 }
1348 lghi(dst, Operand::Zero());
1349 cfdbr(m, dst, double_input);
1350}
1351
1352void MacroAssembler::ConvertFloat32ToInt32(const Register result,
1353 const DoubleRegister double_input,
1354 FPRoundingMode rounding_mode) {
1355 Condition m = Condition(0);
1356 switch (rounding_mode) {
1357 case kRoundToZero:
1358 m = Condition(5);
1359 break;
1360 case kRoundToNearest:
1361 m = Condition(4);
1362 break;
1363 case kRoundToPlusInf:
1364 m = Condition(6);
1365 break;
1366 case kRoundToMinusInf:
1367 m = Condition(7);
1368 break;
1369 default:
1370 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1371 }
1372 lghi(result, Operand::Zero());
1373 cfebr(m, result, double_input);
1374}
1375

1377 const Register result, const DoubleRegister double_input,
1378 FPRoundingMode rounding_mode) {

1380 switch (rounding_mode) {
1381 case kRoundToZero:
1382 m = Condition(5);
1383 break;
1384 case kRoundToNearest:
1385 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1386 case kRoundToPlusInf:
1387 m = Condition(6);
1388 break;
1389 case kRoundToMinusInf:
1390 m = Condition(7);
1391 break;
1392 default:
1393 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1394 }
1395 lghi(result, Operand::Zero());
1396 clfebr(m, Condition(0), result, double_input);
1397}

1475 int prologue_offset) {
1476 {

1489 ShiftLeftU64(ip, count, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
1490 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, ip));
1491}

1499
1500void MacroAssembler::EnterFrame(StackFrame::Type type,
1501 bool load_constant_pool_pointer_reg) {
1502 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1503 // We create a stack frame with:
1504 // Return Addr <-- old sp
1505 // Old FP <-- new fp
1506 // CP
1507 // type
1508 // CodeObject <-- new sp
1509
1510 Register scratch = no_reg;
1511 if (!StackFrame::IsJavaScript(type)) {
1512 scratch = ip;
1513 mov(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
1514 }
1515 PushCommonFrame(scratch);
1516#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1517 if (type == StackFrame::WASM) Push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
1518#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1519}
1520
1521int MacroAssembler::LeaveFrame(StackFrame::Type type, int stack_adjustment) {
1522 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1523 // Drop the execution stack down to the frame pointer and restore
1524 // the caller frame pointer, return address and constant pool pointer.
1525 LoadU64(r14, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
1526 if (is_int20(StandardFrameConstants::kCallerSPOffset + stack_adjustment)) {
1527 lay(r1, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kCallerSPOffset +
1528 stack_adjustment));
1529 } else {
1530 AddS64(r1, fp,
1531 Operand(StandardFrameConstants::kCallerSPOffset + stack_adjustment));
1532 }
1533 LoadU64(fp, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset));
1534 mov(sp, r1);
1535 int frame_ends = pc_offset();
1536 return frame_ends;
1537}
1538
1539// ExitFrame layout (probably wrongish.. needs updating)
1540//
1541// SP -> previousSP
1542// LK reserved
1543// sp_on_exit (for debug?)
1544// oldSP->prev SP
1545// LK
1546// <parameters on stack>
1547
1548// Prior to calling EnterExitFrame, we've got a bunch of parameters
1549// on the stack that we need to wrap a real frame around.. so first
1550// we reserve a slot for LK and push the previous SP which is captured
1551// in the fp register (r11)
1552// Then - we buy a new frame
1553
1554// r14
1555// oldFP <- newFP
1556// SP
1557// Floats
1558// gaps
1559// Args
1560// ABIRes <- newSP
1561void MacroAssembler::EnterExitFrame(Register scratch, int stack_space,
1562 StackFrame::Type frame_type) {
1563 DCHECK(frame_type == StackFrame::EXIT ||
1564 frame_type == StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT ||
1565 frame_type == StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT ||
1566 frame_type == StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT);
1567
1568 // Set up the frame structure on the stack.
1569 DCHECK_EQ(2 * kSystemPointerSize, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerSPDisplacement);
1570 DCHECK_EQ(1 * kSystemPointerSize, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset);
1571 DCHECK_EQ(0 * kSystemPointerSize, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset);
1572
1573 using ER = ExternalReference;
1574
1575 // This is an opportunity to build a frame to wrap
1576 // all of the pushes that have happened inside of V8
1577 // since we were called from C code
1578 mov(r1, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(frame_type)));
1579 PushCommonFrame(r1);
1580 // Reserve room for saved entry sp.
1581 lay(sp, MemOperand(fp, -ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp));
1582
1583 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
1584 StoreU64(MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset), Operand::Zero(),
1585 r1);
1586 }
1587
1588 // Save the frame pointer and the context in top.
1589 ER c_entry_fp_address =
1590 ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
1591 StoreU64(fp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
1592
1593 ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
1594 StoreU64(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
1595
1596 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -(stack_space + 1) * kSystemPointerSize));
1597
1598 // Allocate and align the frame preparing for calling the runtime
1599 // function.
1600 const int frame_alignment = MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment();
1601 if (frame_alignment > 0) {
1602 DCHECK_EQ(frame_alignment, 8);
1603 ClearRightImm(sp, sp, Operand(3)); // equivalent to &= -8
1604 }
1605
1606 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kNumRequiredStackFrameSlots * kSystemPointerSize));
1607 StoreU64(MemOperand(sp), Operand::Zero(), r0);
1608 // Set the exit frame sp value to point just before the return address
1609 // location.
1610 lay(r1, MemOperand(sp, kStackFrameSPSlot * kSystemPointerSize));
1611 StoreU64(r1, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
1612}
1613
1614int MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment() {
1615#if !defined(USE_SIMULATOR)
1616 // Running on the real platform. Use the alignment as mandated by the local
1617 // environment.
1618 // Note: This will break if we ever start generating snapshots on one S390
1619 // platform for another S390 platform with a different alignment.
1620 return base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
1621#else // Simulated
1622 // If we are using the simulator then we should always align to the expected
1623 // alignment. As the simulator is used to generate snapshots we do not know
1624 // if the target platform will need alignment, so this is controlled from a
1625 // flag.
1626 return v8_flags.sim_stack_alignment;
1627#endif
1628}
1629
1630void MacroAssembler::LeaveExitFrame(Register scratch) {
1631 using ER = ExternalReference;
1632
1633 // Restore current context from top and clear it in debug mode.
1634 ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
1635 LoadU64(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
1636
1637#ifdef DEBUG
1638 mov(scratch, Operand(Context::kInvalidContext));
1639 StoreU64(scratch, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
1640#endif
1641
1642 // Clear the top frame.
1643 ER c_entry_fp_address =
1644 ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
1645 mov(scratch, Operand::Zero());
1646 StoreU64(scratch, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
1647
1648 // Tear down the exit frame, pop the arguments, and return.
1649 LeaveFrame(StackFrame::EXIT);
1650}

1652void MacroAssembler::MovFromFloatResult(const DoubleRegister dst) {
1653 Move(dst, d0);
1654}
1655
1656void MacroAssembler::MovFromFloatParameter(const DoubleRegister dst) {
1657 Move(dst, d0);
1658}
1659
1660MemOperand MacroAssembler::StackLimitAsMemOperand(StackLimitKind kind) {
1661 DCHECK(root_array_available());
1662 Isolate* isolate = this->isolate();
1663 ExternalReference limit =
1664 kind == StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit
1665 ? ExternalReference::address_of_real_jslimit(isolate)
1666 : ExternalReference::address_of_jslimit(isolate);
1667 DCHECK(MacroAssembler::IsAddressableThroughRootRegister(isolate, limit));
1668
1669 intptr_t offset =
1670 MacroAssembler::RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate, limit);
1671 CHECK(is_int32(offset));
1672 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, offset);
1673}
1674
1675void MacroAssembler::StackOverflowCheck(Register num_args, Register scratch,
1676 Label* stack_overflow) {
1677 // Check the stack for overflow. We are not trying to catch
1678 // interruptions (e.g. debug break and preemption) here, so the "real stack
1679 // limit" is checked.
1680 LoadU64(scratch, StackLimitAsMemOperand(StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit));
1681 // Make scratch the space we have left. The stack might already be overflowed
1682 // here which will cause scratch to become negative.
1683 SubS64(scratch, sp, scratch);
1684 // Check if the arguments will overflow the stack.
1685 ShiftLeftU64(r0, num_args, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
1686 CmpS64(scratch, r0);
1687 ble(stack_overflow); // Signed comparison.
1688}
1689
1690void MacroAssembler::InvokePrologue(Register expected_parameter_count,
1691 Register actual_parameter_count,
1692 InvokeType type) {
1693 Label regular_invoke;
1694
1695 // r2: actual arguments count
1696 // r3: function (passed through to callee)
1697 // r4: expected arguments count
1698
1699 DCHECK_EQ(actual_parameter_count, r2);
1700 DCHECK_EQ(expected_parameter_count, r4);
1701
1702 // If overapplication or if the actual argument count is equal to the
1703 // formal parameter count, no need to push extra undefined values.
1704 SubS64(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count,
1705 actual_parameter_count);
1706 ble(&regular_invoke);
1707
1708 Label stack_overflow;
1709 Register scratch = r6;
1710 StackOverflowCheck(expected_parameter_count, scratch, &stack_overflow);
1711
1712 // Underapplication. Move the arguments already in the stack, including the
1713 // receiver and the return address.
1714 {
1715 Label copy, check;
1716 Register num = r7, src = r8, dest = ip; // r7 and r8 are context and root.
1717 mov(src, sp);
1718 // Update stack pointer.
1719 ShiftLeftU64(scratch, expected_parameter_count,
1720 Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
1721 SubS64(sp, sp, scratch);
1722 mov(dest, sp);
1723 ltgr(num, actual_parameter_count);
1724 b(&check);
1725 bind(&copy);
1726 LoadU64(r0, MemOperand(src));
1727 lay(src, MemOperand(src, kSystemPointerSize));
1728 StoreU64(r0, MemOperand(dest));
1729 lay(dest, MemOperand(dest, kSystemPointerSize));
1730 SubS64(num, num, Operand(1));
1731 bind(&check);
1732 b(gt, &copy);
1733 }
1734
1735 // Fill remaining expected arguments with undefined values.
1736 LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
1737 {
1738 Label loop;
1739 bind(&loop);
1740 StoreU64(scratch, MemOperand(ip));
1741 lay(ip, MemOperand(ip, kSystemPointerSize));
1742 SubS64(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count, Operand(1));
1743 bgt(&loop);
1744 }
1745 b(&regular_invoke);
1746
1747 bind(&stack_overflow);
1748 {
1749 FrameScope frame(
1750 this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
1751 CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
1752 bkpt(0);
1753 }
1754
1755 bind(&regular_invoke);
1756}
1757
1758void MacroAssembler::CheckDebugHook(Register fun, Register new_target,
1759 Register expected_parameter_count,
1760 Register actual_parameter_count) {
1761 Label skip_hook;
1762
1763 ExternalReference debug_hook_active =
1764 ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate());
1765 Move(r6, debug_hook_active);
1766 tm(MemOperand(r6), Operand(0xFF));
1767 beq(&skip_hook);
1768
1769 {
1770 // Load receiver to pass it later to DebugOnFunctionCall hook.
1771 LoadReceiver(r6);
1772 FrameScope frame(
1773 this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
1774
1775 SmiTag(expected_parameter_count);
1776 Push(expected_parameter_count);
1777
1778 SmiTag(actual_parameter_count);
1779 Push(actual_parameter_count);
1780
1781 if (new_target.is_valid()) {
1782 Push(new_target);
1783 }
1784 Push(fun, fun, r6);
1785 CallRuntime(Runtime::kDebugOnFunctionCall);
1786 Pop(fun);
1787 if (new_target.is_valid()) {
1788 Pop(new_target);
1789 }
1790
1791 Pop(actual_parameter_count);
1792 SmiUntag(actual_parameter_count);
1793
1794 Pop(expected_parameter_count);
1795 SmiUntag(expected_parameter_count);
1796 }
1797 bind(&skip_hook);
1798}
1799
1800void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(Register function, Register new_target,
1801 Register expected_parameter_count,
1802 Register actual_parameter_count,
1803 InvokeType type) {
1804 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
1805 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
1806 DCHECK_EQ(function, r3);
1807 DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == r5);
1808
1809 // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
1810 CheckDebugHook(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
1811 actual_parameter_count);
1812
1813 // Clear the new.target register if not given.
1814 if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
1815 LoadRoot(r5, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
1816 }
1817
1818 InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, type);
1819 // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
1820 // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
1821 // call sites.
1822 constexpr int unused_argument_count = 0;
1823 switch (type) {
1824 case InvokeType::kCall:
1825 CallJSFunction(function, unused_argument_count);
1826 break;
1827 case InvokeType::kJump:
1828 JumpJSFunction(function);
1829 break;
1830 }
1831}
1832
1833void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionWithNewTarget(
1834 Register fun, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
1835 InvokeType type) {
1836 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
1837 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
1838
1839 // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in r3.
1840 DCHECK_EQ(fun, r3);
1841
1842 Register expected_reg = r4;
1843 Register temp_reg = r6;
1844 LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(fun, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
1845 LoadTaggedField(temp_reg,
1846 FieldMemOperand(fun, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset));
1847 LoadU16(expected_reg,
1848 FieldMemOperand(temp_reg,
1849 SharedFunctionInfo::kFormalParameterCountOffset));
1850
1851 InvokeFunctionCode(fun, new_target, expected_reg, actual_parameter_count,
1852 type);
1853}
1854
1855void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(Register function,
1856 Register expected_parameter_count,
1857 Register actual_parameter_count,
1858 InvokeType type) {
1859 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
1860 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
1861
1862 // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in r3.
1863 DCHECK_EQ(function, r3);
1864
1865 // Get the function and setup the context.
1866 LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
1867
1868 InvokeFunctionCode(r3, no_reg, expected_parameter_count,
1869 actual_parameter_count, type);
1870}
1871
1872void MacroAssembler::PushStackHandler() {
1873 // Adjust this code if not the case.
1874 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kSize == 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
1875 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0 * kSystemPointerSize);
1876
1877 // Link the current handler as the next handler.
1878 Move(r7,
1879 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate()));
1880
1881 // Buy the full stack frame for 5 slots.
1882 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -StackHandlerConstants::kSize));
1883
1884 // Store padding.
1885 lghi(r0, Operand::Zero());
1886 StoreU64(r0, MemOperand(sp)); // Padding.
1887
1888 // Copy the old handler into the next handler slot.
1889 MoveChar(MemOperand(sp, StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset), MemOperand(r7),
1890 Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
1891 // Set this new handler as the current one.
1892 StoreU64(sp, MemOperand(r7));
1893}
1894
1895void MacroAssembler::PopStackHandler() {
1896 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kSize == 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
1897 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0);
1898
1899 // Pop the Next Handler into r3 and store it into Handler Address reference.
1900 Pop(r3);
1901 Move(ip,
1902 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate()));
1903 StoreU64(r3, MemOperand(ip));
1904
1905 Drop(1); // Drop padding.
1906}
1907
1908void MacroAssembler::IsObjectType(Register object, Register scratch1,
1909 Register scratch2, InstanceType type) {
1910 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1911 CompareObjectType(object, scratch1, scratch2, type);
1912}
1913
1914void MacroAssembler::CompareObjectTypeRange(Register object, Register map,
1915 Register type_reg, Register scratch,
1916 InstanceType lower_limit,
1917 InstanceType upper_limit) {
1918 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1919 LoadMap(map, object);
1920 CompareInstanceTypeRange(map, type_reg, scratch, lower_limit, upper_limit);
1921}
1922
1923void MacroAssembler::CompareRange(Register value, Register scratch,
1924 unsigned lower_limit, unsigned higher_limit) {
1925 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1926 DCHECK_LT(lower_limit, higher_limit);
1927 if (lower_limit != 0) {
1928 mov(scratch, value);
1929 slgfi(scratch, Operand(lower_limit));
1930 CmpU64(scratch, Operand(higher_limit - lower_limit));
1931 } else {
1932 CmpU64(value, Operand(higher_limit));
1933 }
1934}
1935
1936void MacroAssembler::CompareInstanceTypeRange(Register map, Register type_reg,
1937 Register scratch,
1938 InstanceType lower_limit,
1939 InstanceType higher_limit) {
1940 DCHECK_LT(lower_limit, higher_limit);
1941 LoadU16(type_reg, FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
1942 CompareRange(type_reg, scratch, lower_limit, higher_limit);
1943}
1944
1945void MacroAssembler::CompareRoot(Register obj, RootIndex index) {
1946 if (!base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
1947 RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot)) {
1948 // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
1949 LoadRoot(r0, index);
1950 CmpU64(obj, r0);
1951 return;
1952 }
1953 return CompareTaggedRoot(obj, index);
1954}
1955
1956void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedRoot(Register obj, RootIndex index) {
1957 if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
1958 CompareTagged(obj, Operand(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index)));
1959 return;
1960 }
1961 int32_t offset = RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index);
1962#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
1963 offset += (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? kTaggedSize : 0);
1964#endif
1965 CompareTagged(obj, MemOperand(kRootRegister, offset));
1966}
1967
1968void MacroAssembler::JumpIfIsInRange(Register value, Register scratch,
1969 unsigned lower_limit,
1970 unsigned higher_limit,
1971 Label* on_in_range) {
1972 CompareRange(value, scratch, lower_limit, higher_limit);
1973 ble(on_in_range);
1974}
1975
1976void MacroAssembler::TruncateDoubleToI(Isolate* isolate, Zone* zone,
1977 Register result,
1978 DoubleRegister double_input,
1979 StubCallMode stub_mode) {
1980 Label done;
1981
1982 TryInlineTruncateDoubleToI(result, double_input, &done);
1983
1984 // If we fell through then inline version didn't succeed - call stub instead.
1985 push(r14);
1986 // Put input on stack.
1987 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kDoubleSize));
1988 StoreF64(double_input, MemOperand(sp));
1989
1990#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1991 if (stub_mode == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
1992 Call(static_cast<Address>(Builtin::kDoubleToI), RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
1993#else
1994 // For balance.
1995 if (false) {
1996#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1997 } else {
1998 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kDoubleToI);
1999 }
2000
2001 LoadU64(result, MemOperand(sp, 0));
2002 la(sp, MemOperand(sp, kDoubleSize));
2003 pop(r14);
2004
2005 bind(&done);
2006}
2007
2008void MacroAssembler::TryInlineTruncateDoubleToI(Register result,
2009 DoubleRegister double_input,
2010 Label* done) {
2011 ConvertDoubleToInt64(result, double_input);
2012
2013 // Test for overflow
2014 TestIfInt32(result);
2015 beq(done);
2016}
2017
2018namespace {
2019
2020#ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2021
2022void TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(MacroAssembler* masm,
2023 Register optimized_code_entry,
2024 Register scratch) {
2025 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2026 // -- r2 : actual argument count
2027 // -- r5 : new target (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
2028 // -- r3 : target function (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
2029 // -----------------------------------
2030 DCHECK(!AreAliased(r3, r5, optimized_code_entry, scratch));
2031
2032 Register closure = r3;
2033 Label heal_optimized_code_slot;
2034
2035 // If the optimized code is cleared, go to runtime to update the optimization
2036 // marker field.
2037 __ LoadWeakValue(optimized_code_entry, optimized_code_entry,
2038 &heal_optimized_code_slot);
2039
2040 // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
2041 __ LoadTaggedField(
2042 optimized_code_entry,
2043 FieldMemOperand(optimized_code_entry, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
2044
2045 // Check if the optimized code is marked for deopt. If it is, call the
2046 // runtime to clear it.
2047 {
2048 __ TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(optimized_code_entry, scratch);
2049 __ bne(&heal_optimized_code_slot);
2050 }
2051
2052 // Optimized code is good, get it into the closure and link the closure
2053 // into the optimized functions list, then tail call the optimized code.
2054 __ ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(optimized_code_entry, closure, scratch,
2055 r7);
2056 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == r4, "ABI mismatch");
2057 __ LoadCodeInstructionStart(r4, optimized_code_entry);
2058 __ Jump(r4);
2059
2060 // Optimized code slot contains deoptimized code or code is cleared and
2061 // optimized code marker isn't updated. Evict the code, update the marker
2062 // and re-enter the closure's code.
2063 __ bind(&heal_optimized_code_slot);
2064 __ GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kHealOptimizedCodeSlot);
2065}
2066
2067#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2068
2069} // namespace

2081 Assert(eq, AbortReason::kExpectedFeedbackVector);

2093
2094// Optimized code is good, get it into the closure and link the closure
2095// into the optimized functions list, then tail call the optimized code.
2096void MacroAssembler::ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(
2097 Register optimized_code, Register closure, Register scratch1,
2098 Register slot_address) {
2099#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2100 UNREACHABLE();
2101#else
2102 DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code, closure, scratch1, slot_address));
2103 DCHECK_EQ(closure, kJSFunctionRegister);
2104 DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code, closure));
2105 // Store code entry in the closure.
2106 StoreTaggedField(optimized_code,
2107 FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset), r0);
2108 // Write barrier clobbers scratch1 below.
2109 Register value = scratch1;
2110 mov(value, optimized_code);
2111
2112 RecordWriteField(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset, value, slot_address,
2113 kLRHasNotBeenSaved, SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore,
2114 SmiCheck::kOmit);
2115#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2116}
2117
2118void MacroAssembler::GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(
2119 Runtime::FunctionId function_id) {
2120 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
2121 // -- r2 : actual argument count
2122 // -- r3 : target function (preserved for callee)
2123 // -- r5 : new target (preserved for callee)
2124 // -----------------------------------
2125 {
2126 FrameAndConstantPoolScope scope(this, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
2127 // Push a copy of the target function, the new target and the actual
2128 // argument count.
2129 // Push function as parameter to the runtime call.
2130 SmiTag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
2131 Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
2132 kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister, kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
2133
2134 CallRuntime(function_id, 1);
2135 mov(r4, r2);
2136
2137 // Restore target function, new target and actual argument count.
2138 Pop(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
2139 kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
2140 SmiUntag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
2141 }
2142 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == r4, "ABI mismatch");
2143 JumpCodeObject(r4);
2144}
2145
2146#ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2147
2148// Read off the flags in the feedback vector and check if there
2149// is optimized code or a tiering state that needs to be processed.
2150Condition MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndCheckIfNeedsProcessing(
2151 Register flags, Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind) {
2152 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2153 DCHECK(!AreAliased(flags, feedback_vector));
2154 DCHECK(CodeKindCanTierUp(current_code_kind));
2155 LoadU16(flags,
2156 FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset));
2157 uint32_t kFlagsMask = FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested |
2158 FeedbackVector::kFlagsMaybeHasTurbofanCode |
2159 FeedbackVector::kFlagsLogNextExecution;
2160 if (current_code_kind != CodeKind::MAGLEV) {
2161 kFlagsMask |= FeedbackVector::kFlagsMaybeHasMaglevCode;
2162 }
2163 CHECK(is_uint16(kFlagsMask));
2164 tmll(flags, Operand(kFlagsMask));
2165 return Condition(7);
2166}
2167
2168// Read off the flags in the feedback vector and check if there
2169// is optimized code or a tiering state that needs to be processed.
2170void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndJumpIfNeedsProcessing(
2171 Register flags, Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind,
2172 Label* flags_need_processing) {
2173 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2174 b(LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndCheckIfNeedsProcessing(flags, feedback_vector,
2175 current_code_kind),
2176 flags_need_processing);
2177}
2178
2179void MacroAssembler::OptimizeCodeOrTailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(
2180 Register flags, Register feedback_vector) {
2181 DCHECK(!AreAliased(flags, feedback_vector));
2182 Label maybe_has_optimized_code, maybe_needs_logging;
2183 // Check if optimized code is available
2184 TestBitMask(flags, FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested, r0);
2185 beq(&maybe_needs_logging);
2186
2187 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kCompileOptimized);
2188
2189 bind(&maybe_needs_logging);
2190 TestBitMask(flags, FeedbackVector::LogNextExecutionBit::kMask, r0);
2191 beq(&maybe_has_optimized_code);
2192 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kFunctionLogNextExecution);
2193
2194 bind(&maybe_has_optimized_code);
2195 Register optimized_code_entry = flags;
2196 LoadTaggedField(optimized_code_entry,
2197 FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
2198 FeedbackVector::kMaybeOptimizedCodeOffset));
2199 TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(this, optimized_code_entry, r1);
2200}

2202#endif // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2203
2204void MacroAssembler::CallRuntime(const Runtime::Function* f,
2205 int num_arguments) {
2206 // All parameters are on the stack. r2 has the return value after call.
2207
2208 // If the expected number of arguments of the runtime function is
2209 // constant, we check that the actual number of arguments match the
2210 // expectation.
2211 CHECK(f->nargs < 0 || f->nargs == num_arguments);
2212
2213 // TODO(1236192): Most runtime routines don't need the number of
2214 // arguments passed in because it is constant. At some point we
2215 // should remove this need and make the runtime routine entry code
2216 // smarter.
2217 mov(r2, Operand(num_arguments));
2218 Move(r3, ExternalReference::Create(f));
2219 bool switch_to_central_stack = options().is_wasm;
2220 CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(f->result_size, switch_to_central_stack));
2221}
2222
2223void MacroAssembler::TailCallRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId fid) {
2224 const Runtime::Function* function = Runtime::FunctionForId(fid);
2225 DCHECK_EQ(1, function->result_size);
2226 if (function->nargs >= 0) {
2227 mov(r2, Operand(function->nargs));
2228 }
2229 JumpToExternalReference(ExternalReference::Create(fid));
2230}
2231
2232void MacroAssembler::JumpToExternalReference(const ExternalReference& builtin,
2233 bool builtin_exit_frame) {
2234 Move(r3, builtin);
2235 TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CEntry(1, ArgvMode::kStack, builtin_exit_frame));
2236}
2237
2238void MacroAssembler::LoadWeakValue(Register out, Register in,
2239 Label* target_if_cleared) {
2240 CmpS32(in, Operand(kClearedWeakHeapObjectLower32));
2241 beq(target_if_cleared);
2242
2243 AndP(out, in, Operand(~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
2244}
2245
2246void MacroAssembler::EmitIncrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
2247 Register scratch1,
2248 Register scratch2) {
2249 DCHECK(value > 0 && is_int8(value));
2250 if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
2251 Move(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
2252 // @TODO(john.yan): can be optimized by asi()
2253 LoadS32(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
2254 AddS64(scratch1, Operand(value));
2255 StoreU32(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
2256 }
2257}
2258
2259void MacroAssembler::EmitDecrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
2260 Register scratch1,
2261 Register scratch2) {
2262 DCHECK(value > 0 && is_int8(value));
2263 if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
2264 Move(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
2265 // @TODO(john.yan): can be optimized by asi()
2266 LoadS32(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
2267 AddS64(scratch1, Operand(-value));
2268 StoreU32(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
2269 }
2270}
2271
2272void MacroAssembler::Check(Condition cond, AbortReason reason, CRegister cr) {
2273 Label L;
2274 b(to_condition(cond), &L);
2275 Abort(reason);
2276 // will not return here
2277 bind(&L);
2278}
2279
2280void MacroAssembler::Abort(AbortReason reason) {
2281 Label abort_start;
2282 bind(&abort_start);
2283 if (v8_flags.code_comments) {
2284 const char* msg = GetAbortReason(reason);
2285 RecordComment("Abort message: ");
2286 RecordComment(msg);
2287 }
2288
2289 // Avoid emitting call to builtin if requested.
2290 if (trap_on_abort()) {
2291 stop();
2292 return;
2293 }
2294
2295 if (should_abort_hard()) {
2296 // We don't care if we constructed a frame. Just pretend we did.
2297 FrameScope assume_frame(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
2298 lgfi(r2, Operand(static_cast<int>(reason)));
2299 PrepareCallCFunction(1, 0, r3);
2300#if V8_OS_ZOS
2301 CallCFunction(ExternalReference::abort_with_reason(), 1, 0);
2302#else
2303 Move(r3, ExternalReference::abort_with_reason());
2304 // Use Call directly to avoid any unneeded overhead. The function won't
2305 // return anyway.
2306 Call(r3);
2307#endif
2308 return;
2309 }
2310
2311 LoadSmiLiteral(r3, Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(reason)));
2312
2313 {
2314 // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
2315 // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
2316 FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
2317 if (root_array_available()) {
2318 // Generate an indirect call via builtins entry table here in order to
2319 // ensure that the interpreter_entry_return_pc_offset is the same for
2320 // InterpreterEntryTrampoline and InterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling
2321 // when v8_flags.debug_code is enabled.
2322 LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort, ip);
2323 Call(ip);
2324 } else {
2325 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort);
2326 }
2327 }
2328 // will not return here
2329}

2331void MacroAssembler::LoadCompressedMap(Register destination, Register object) {
2332 CHECK(COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL);
2333 LoadU32(destination, FieldMemOperand(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
2334}
2335
2336void MacroAssembler::LoadMap(Register destination, Register object) {
2337 LoadTaggedField(destination, FieldMemOperand(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
2338}
2339
2340void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVector(Register dst, Register closure,
2341 Register scratch, Label* fbv_undef) {
2342 Label done;
2343
2344 // Load the feedback vector from the closure.
2345 LoadTaggedField(dst,
2346 FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset));
2347 LoadTaggedField(dst, FieldMemOperand(dst, FeedbackCell::kValueOffset));
2348
2349 // Check if feedback vector is valid.
2350 IsObjectType(dst, scratch, scratch, FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE);
2351 b(eq, &done);
2352
2353 // Not valid, load undefined.
2354 LoadRoot(dst, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2355 b(fbv_undef);
2356
2357 bind(&done);
2358}

2360void MacroAssembler::LoadNativeContextSlot(Register dst, int index) {
2361 LoadMap(dst, cp);
2362 LoadTaggedField(
2363 dst, FieldMemOperand(
2364 dst, Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset));
2365 LoadTaggedField(dst, MemOperand(dst, Context::SlotOffset(index)));
2366}

2413void MacroAssembler::AssertConstructor(Register object, Register scratch) {
2414 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
2415 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
2416 TestIfSmi(object);
2417 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAConstructor);
2418 LoadMap(scratch, object);
2419 tm(FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kBitFieldOffset),
2420 Operand(Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kMask));
2421 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAConstructor);

2425void MacroAssembler::AssertFunction(Register object) {
2426 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
2427 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
2428 TestIfSmi(object);
2429 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAFunction, cr0);
2430 push(object);
2431 LoadMap(object, object);
2432 CompareInstanceTypeRange(object, object, object, FIRST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE,
2433 LAST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE);
2434 pop(object);
2435 Check(le, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAFunction);
2436 }

2443 TestIfSmi(object);
2444 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAFunction);
2445 push(object);
2446 LoadMap(object, object);
2447 CompareInstanceTypeRange(object, object, object,
2448 FIRST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE,
2449 LAST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE);

2466void MacroAssembler::AssertGeneratorObject(Register object) {
2467 if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
2468 TestIfSmi(object);
2469 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAGeneratorObject, cr0);
2470
2471 // Load map
2472 Register map = object;
2473 push(object);
2474 LoadMap(map, object);
2475
2476 // Check if JSGeneratorObject
2477 Register scratch = object;
2478 CompareInstanceTypeRange(map, scratch, scratch,
2479 FIRST_JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE,
2480 LAST_JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE);
2481 // Restore generator object to register and perform assertion
2482 pop(object);
2483 Check(le, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAGeneratorObject);
2484}

2486void MacroAssembler::AssertUndefinedOrAllocationSite(Register object,
2487 Register scratch) {
2488 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
2489 Label done_checking;
2490 AssertNotSmi(object);
2491 CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2492 beq(&done_checking, Label::kNear);
2493 LoadMap(scratch, object);
2494 CompareInstanceType(scratch, scratch, ALLOCATION_SITE_TYPE);
2495 Assert(eq, AbortReason::kExpectedUndefinedOrCell);
2496 bind(&done_checking);
2497 }

2500void MacroAssembler::AssertJSAny(Register object, Register map_tmp,
2501 Register tmp, AbortReason abort_reason) {
2502 if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
2503
2504 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2505 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, map_tmp, tmp));
2506 Label ok;
2507
2508 JumpIfSmi(object, &ok);
2509
2510 LoadMap(map_tmp, object);
2511 CompareInstanceType(map_tmp, tmp, LAST_NAME_TYPE);
2512 ble(&ok);
2513
2514 CompareInstanceType(map_tmp, tmp, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
2515 bge(&ok);
2516
2517 CompareRoot(map_tmp, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
2518 beq(&ok);
2519
2520 CompareRoot(map_tmp, RootIndex::kBigIntMap);
2521 beq(&ok);
2522
2523 CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2524 beq(&ok);
2525
2526 CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
2527 beq(&ok);
2528
2529 CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
2530 beq(&ok);
2531
2532 CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kNullValue);
2533 beq(&ok);
2534
2535 Abort(abort_reason);
2536
2537 bind(&ok);
2538}
