2541
2542int MacroAssembler::CalculateStackPassedWords(int num_reg_arguments,
2543 int num_double_arguments) {
2544 int stack_passed_words = 0;
2545 if (num_double_arguments > DoubleRegister::kNumRegisters) {
2546 stack_passed_words +=
2547 2 * (num_double_arguments - DoubleRegister::kNumRegisters);
2548 }
2549 // Up to five simple arguments are passed in registers r2..r6
2550 if (num_reg_arguments > kRegisterPassedArguments) {
2551 stack_passed_words += num_reg_arguments - kRegisterPassedArguments;
2552 }
2553 return stack_passed_words;
2554}
2555
2556void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
2557 int num_double_arguments,
2558 Register scratch) {
2559 int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
2560 int stack_passed_arguments =
2561 CalculateStackPassedWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
2562 int stack_space = kNumRequiredStackFrameSlots;
2563 if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
2564 // Make stack end at alignment and make room for stack arguments
2565 // -- preserving original value of sp.
2566 mov(scratch, sp);
2567 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -(stack_passed_arguments + 1) * kSystemPointerSize));
2568 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
2569 ClearRightImm(sp, sp,
2570 Operand(base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment)));
2571 StoreU64(scratch,
2572 MemOperand(sp, (stack_passed_arguments)*kSystemPointerSize));
2573 } else {
2574 stack_space += stack_passed_arguments;
2575 }
2576 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, (-stack_space) * kSystemPointerSize));
2577}
2578
2579void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
2580 Register scratch) {
2581 PrepareCallCFunction(num_reg_arguments, 0, scratch);
2582}
2583
2584void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatParameter(DoubleRegister src) { Move(d0, src); }
2585
2586void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatResult(DoubleRegister src) { Move(d0, src); }
2587
2588void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatParameters(DoubleRegister src1,
2589 DoubleRegister src2) {
2590 if (src2 == d0) {
2591 DCHECK(src1 != d2);
2592 Move(d2, src2);
2593 Move(d0, src1);
2594 } else {
2595 Move(d0, src1);
2596 Move(d2, src2);
2597 }
2598}
2599
2600int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(ExternalReference function,
2601 int num_reg_arguments,
2602 int num_double_arguments,
2603 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
2604 bool has_function_descriptor,
2605 Label* return_label) {
2606 Move(ip, function);
2607 return CallCFunction(ip, num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments,
2608 set_isolate_data_slots, has_function_descriptor,
2609 return_label);
2610}
2611
2612int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(Register function, int num_reg_arguments,
2613 int num_double_arguments,
2614 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
2615 bool has_function_descriptor,
2616 Label* return_label) {
2617 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2618 DCHECK_LE(num_reg_arguments + num_double_arguments, kMaxCParameters);
2619 DCHECK(has_frame());
2620
2621#if V8_OS_ZOS
2622 // Shuffle input arguments
2623 mov(r1, r2);
2624 mov(r2, r3);
2625 mov(r3, r4);
2626
2627 // XPLINK treats r7 as voliatile return register, but r14 as preserved
2628 // Since Linux is the other way around, perserve r7 value in r14 across
2629 // the call.
2630 mov(r14, r7);
2631
2632 // XPLINK linkage requires args in r5,r6,r7,r8,r9 to be passed on the stack.
2633 // However, for DirectAPI C calls, there may not be stack slots
2634 // for these 4th and 5th parameters if num_reg_arguments are less
2635 // than 3. In that case, we need to still preserve r5/r6 into
2636 // register save area, as they are considered volatile in XPLINK.
2637 if (num_reg_arguments == 4) {
2638 StoreU64(r5, MemOperand(sp, 19 * kSystemPointerSize));
2639 StoreU64(r6, MemOperand(sp, 6 * kSystemPointerSize));
2640 } else if (num_reg_arguments >= 5) {
2641 // Save original r5 - r6 to Stack, r7 - r9 already saved to Stack
2642 StoreMultipleP(r5, r6, MemOperand(sp, 19 * kSystemPointerSize));
2643 } else {
2644 StoreMultipleP(r5, r6, MemOperand(sp, 5 * kSystemPointerSize));
2645 }
2646#endif
2647
2648 Label get_pc;
2649
2650 if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
2651 // Save the frame pointer and PC so that the stack layout remains iterable,
2652 // even without an ExitFrame which normally exists between JS and C frames.
2653 // See x64 code for reasoning about how to address the isolate data fields.
2654 larl(r0, &get_pc);
2655 CHECK(root_array_available());
2656 StoreU64(r0,
2657 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerPC));
2658 StoreU64(fp,
2659 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
2660 }
2661
2662#if V8_OS_ZOS
2663 // Set up the system stack pointer with the XPLINK bias.
2664 lay(r4, MemOperand(sp, -kStackPointerBias));
2665
2666 Register dest = function;
2667 if (has_function_descriptor) {
2668 LoadMultipleP(r5, r6, MemOperand(function));
2669 dest = r6;
2670 }
2671#else
2672 // Just call directly. The function called cannot cause a GC, or
2673 // allow preemption, so the return address in the link register
2674 // stays correct.
2675 Register dest = function;
2676 if (ABI_CALL_VIA_IP) {
2677 Move(ip, function);
2678 dest = ip;
2679 }
2680#endif
2681
2682#if V8_OS_ZOS
2683 if (has_function_descriptor) {
2684 // Branch to target via indirect branch
2685 basr(r7, dest);
2686 nop(BASR_CALL_TYPE_NOP);
2687 } else {
2688 basr(r7, dest);
2689 }
2690
2691 // Restore r5-r9 from the appropriate stack locations (see notes above).
2692 if (num_reg_arguments == 4) {
2693 LoadU64(r5, MemOperand(sp, 19 * kSystemPointerSize));
2694 LoadU64(r6, MemOperand(sp, 6 * kSystemPointerSize));
2695 } else if (num_reg_arguments >= 5) {
2696 LoadMultipleP(r5, r6, MemOperand(sp, 19 * kSystemPointerSize));
2697 } else {
2698 LoadMultipleP(r5, r6, MemOperand(sp, 5 * kSystemPointerSize));
2699 }
2700
2701 // Restore original r7
2702 mov(r7, r14);
2703
2704 // Shuffle the result
2705 mov(r2, r3);
2706#else
2707 Call(dest);
2708#endif
2709
2710 int call_pc_offset = pc_offset();
2711 bind(&get_pc);
2712 if (return_label) bind(return_label);
2713
2714 if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
2715 // We don't unset the PC; the FP is the source of truth.
2716 Register zero_scratch = r0;
2717 lghi(zero_scratch, Operand::Zero());
2718
2719 StoreU64(zero_scratch,
2720 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
2721 }
2722
2723 int stack_passed_arguments =
2724 CalculateStackPassedWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
2725 int stack_space = kNumRequiredStackFrameSlots + stack_passed_arguments;
2726 if (ActivationFrameAlignment() > kSystemPointerSize) {
2727 // Load the original stack pointer (pre-alignment) from the stack
2728 LoadU64(sp, MemOperand(sp, stack_space * kSystemPointerSize));
2729 } else {
2730 la(sp, MemOperand(sp, stack_space * kSystemPointerSize));
2731 }
2732
2733 return call_pc_offset;
2734}

2751
2752void MacroAssembler::CheckPageFlag(
2753 Register object,
2754 Register scratch, // scratch may be same register as object
2755 int mask, Condition cc, Label* condition_met) {
2756 DCHECK(cc == ne || cc == eq);
2757 ClearRightImm(scratch, object, Operand(kPageSizeBits));
2758
2759 if (base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(mask)) {
2760 // If it's a power of two, we can use Test-Under-Mask Memory-Imm form
2761 // which allows testing of a single byte in memory.
2762 int32_t byte_offset = 4;
2763 uint32_t shifted_mask = mask;
2764 // Determine the byte offset to be tested
2765 if (mask <= 0x80) {
2766 byte_offset = kSystemPointerSize - 1;
2767 } else if (mask < 0x8000) {
2768 byte_offset = kSystemPointerSize - 2;
2769 shifted_mask = mask >> 8;
2770 } else if (mask < 0x800000) {
2771 byte_offset = kSystemPointerSize - 3;
2772 shifted_mask = mask >> 16;
2773 } else {
2774 byte_offset = kSystemPointerSize - 4;
2775 shifted_mask = mask >> 24;
2776 }
2777#if V8_TARGET_LITTLE_ENDIAN
2778 // Reverse the byte_offset if emulating on little endian platform
2779 byte_offset = kSystemPointerSize - byte_offset - 1;
2780#endif
2781 tm(MemOperand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset() + byte_offset),
2782 Operand(shifted_mask));
2783 } else {
2784 LoadU64(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset()));
2785 AndP(r0, scratch, Operand(mask));
2786 }
2787 // Should be okay to remove rc
2788
2789 if (cc == ne) {
2790 bne(condition_met);
2791 }
2792 if (cc == eq) {
2793 beq(condition_met);
2794 }
2795}
2796
2797Register GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(Register reg1, Register reg2, Register reg3,
2798 Register reg4, Register reg5,
2799 Register reg6) {
2800 RegList regs = {reg1, reg2, reg3, reg4, reg5, reg6};
2801
2802 const RegisterConfiguration* config = RegisterConfiguration::Default();
2803 for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_general_registers(); ++i) {
2804 int code = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
2805 Register candidate = Register::from_code(code);
2806 if (regs.has(candidate)) continue;
2807 return candidate;
2808 }
2809 UNREACHABLE();
2810}
2811
2812void MacroAssembler::mov(Register dst, Register src) { lgr(dst, src); }
2813
2814void MacroAssembler::mov(Register dst, const Operand& src) {
2815 int64_t value = 0;
2816
2817 if (src.is_heap_number_request()) {
2818 RequestHeapNumber(src.heap_number_request());
2819 } else {
2820 value = src.immediate();
2821 }
2822
2823 if (src.rmode() != RelocInfo::NO_INFO) {
2824 // some form of relocation needed
2825 RecordRelocInfo(src.rmode(), value);
2826 }
2827
2828 int32_t hi_32 = static_cast<int32_t>(value >> 32);
2829 int32_t lo_32 = static_cast<int32_t>(value);
2830
2831 if (src.rmode() == RelocInfo::NO_INFO) {
2832 if (hi_32 == 0) {
2833 if (is_uint16(lo_32)) {
2834 llill(dst, Operand(lo_32));
2835 return;
2836 }
2837 llilf(dst, Operand(lo_32));
2838 return;
2839 } else if (lo_32 == 0) {
2840 if (is_uint16(hi_32)) {
2841 llihl(dst, Operand(hi_32));
2842 return;
2843 }
2844 llihf(dst, Operand(hi_32));
2845 return;
2846 } else if (is_int16(value)) {
2847 lghi(dst, Operand(value));
2848 return;
2849 } else if (is_int32(value)) {
2850 lgfi(dst, Operand(value));
2851 return;
2852 }
2853 }
2854
2855 iihf(dst, Operand(hi_32));
2856 iilf(dst, Operand(lo_32));
2857}

2866 }

3115void MacroAssembler::MulHighS64(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3116 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MISC_INSTR_EXT2)) {
3117 mgrk(r0, src1, src2);
3118 lgr(dst, r0);
3119 } else {
3120 SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode = SaveFPRegsMode::kSave;
3121 PushCallerSaved(fp_mode, ip);
3122 Push(src1, src2);
3123 Pop(r2, r3);
3124 {
3125 FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
3126 PrepareCallCFunction(2, 0, r0);
3127 CallCFunction(ExternalReference::int64_mul_high_function(), 2, 0);
3128 }
3129 mov(r0, r2);
3130 PopCallerSaved(fp_mode, ip);
3131 mov(dst, r0);
3132 }
3133}

3170 if (is_int16(opnd.immediate()))
3171 ahi(dst, opnd);
3172 else
3173 afi(dst, opnd);
3174}

3179 aghi(dst, opnd);

3184void MacroAssembler::AddS32(Register dst, Register src, int32_t opnd) {
3185 AddS32(dst, src, Operand(opnd));
3186}
3187
3188// Add 32-bit (Register dst = Register src + Immediate opnd)
3189void MacroAssembler::AddS32(Register dst, Register src, const Operand& opnd) {
3190 if (dst != src) {
3191 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS) && is_int16(opnd.immediate())) {
3192 ahik(dst, src, opnd);
3193 return;
3194 }
3195 lr(dst, src);
3196 }
3197 AddS32(dst, opnd);
3198}

3200void MacroAssembler::AddS64(Register dst, Register src, int32_t opnd) {
3201 AddS64(dst, src, Operand(opnd));
3202}

3204// Add Pointer Size (Register dst = Register src + Immediate opnd)
3205void MacroAssembler::AddS64(Register dst, Register src, const Operand& opnd) {
3206 if (dst != src) {
3207 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS) && is_int16(opnd.immediate())) {
3208 aghik(dst, src, opnd);
3209 return;
3210 }
3211 mov(dst, src);
3212 }
3213 AddS64(dst, opnd);
3214}
3215
3216// Add 32-bit (Register dst = Register dst + Register src)
3217void MacroAssembler::AddS32(Register dst, Register src) { ar(dst, src); }
3218
3219// Add Pointer Size (Register dst = Register dst + Register src)
3220void MacroAssembler::AddS64(Register dst, Register src) { agr(dst, src); }
3221
3222// Add 32-bit (Register dst = Register src1 + Register src2)
3223void MacroAssembler::AddS32(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3224 if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) {
3225 // We prefer to generate AR/AGR, over the non clobbering ARK/AGRK
3226 // as AR is a smaller instruction
3227 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3228 ark(dst, src1, src2);
3229 return;
3230 } else {
3231 lr(dst, src1);
3232 }
3233 } else if (dst == src2) {
3234 src2 = src1;
3235 }
3236 ar(dst, src2);
3237}
3238
3239// Add Pointer Size (Register dst = Register src1 + Register src2)
3240void MacroAssembler::AddS64(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3241 if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) {
3242 // We prefer to generate AR/AGR, over the non clobbering ARK/AGRK
3243 // as AR is a smaller instruction
3244 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3245 agrk(dst, src1, src2);
3246 return;
3247 } else {
3248 mov(dst, src1);
3249 }
3250 } else if (dst == src2) {
3251 src2 = src1;
3252 }
3253 agr(dst, src2);
3254}

3258 DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3259 if (is_uint12(opnd.offset()))
3260 a(dst, opnd);
3261 else
3262 ay(dst, opnd);
3263}

3265// Add Pointer Size (Register-Memory)
3266void MacroAssembler::AddS64(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {

3268 ag(dst, opnd);
3269}

3277}

3287//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3288// Add Logical Instructions
3289//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3290
3291// Add Logical 32-bit (Register dst = Register src1 + Register src2)
3292void MacroAssembler::AddU32(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3293 if (dst != src2 && dst != src1) {
3294 lr(dst, src1);
3295 alr(dst, src2);
3296 } else if (dst != src2) {
3297 // dst == src1
3298 DCHECK(dst == src1);
3299 alr(dst, src2);
3300 } else {
3301 // dst == src2
3302 DCHECK(dst == src2);
3303 alr(dst, src1);
3304 }
3305}
3306
3307// Add Logical 32-bit (Register dst = Register dst + Immediate opnd)
3308void MacroAssembler::AddU32(Register dst, const Operand& imm) {
3309 alfi(dst, imm);
3310}
3311
3312// Add Logical Pointer Size (Register dst = Register dst + Immediate opnd)
3313void MacroAssembler::AddU64(Register dst, const Operand& imm) {
3314 algfi(dst, imm);
3315}
3316
3317void MacroAssembler::AddU64(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3318 if (dst != src2 && dst != src1) {
3319 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3320 algrk(dst, src1, src2);
3321 } else {
3322 lgr(dst, src1);
3323 algr(dst, src2);
3324 }
3325 } else if (dst != src2) {
3326 // dst == src1
3327 DCHECK(dst == src1);
3328 algr(dst, src2);
3329 } else {
3330 // dst == src2
3331 DCHECK(dst == src2);
3332 algr(dst, src1);
3333 }
3334}
3335
3336// Add Logical 32-bit (Register-Memory)
3337void MacroAssembler::AddU32(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3338 DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3339 if (is_uint12(opnd.offset()))
3340 al_z(dst, opnd);
3341 else
3342 aly(dst, opnd);
3343}
3344
3345// Add Logical Pointer Size (Register-Memory)
3346void MacroAssembler::AddU64(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3347 DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3348 alg(dst, opnd);
3349}

3351//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3352// Subtract Instructions
3353//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3354
3355// Subtract Logical 32-bit (Register dst = Register src1 - Register src2)
3356void MacroAssembler::SubU32(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3357 if (dst != src2 && dst != src1) {
3358 lr(dst, src1);
3359 slr(dst, src2);
3360 } else if (dst != src2) {
3361 // dst == src1
3362 DCHECK(dst == src1);
3363 slr(dst, src2);
3364 } else {
3365 // dst == src2
3366 DCHECK(dst == src2);
3367 lr(r0, dst);
3368 SubU32(dst, src1, r0);
3369 }
3370}
3371
3372// Subtract 32-bit (Register dst = Register dst - Immediate opnd)
3373void MacroAssembler::SubS32(Register dst, const Operand& imm) {
3374 AddS32(dst, Operand(-(imm.immediate())));
3375}
3376
3377// Subtract Pointer Size (Register dst = Register dst - Immediate opnd)
3378void MacroAssembler::SubS64(Register dst, const Operand& imm) {
3379 AddS64(dst, Operand(-(imm.immediate())));
3380}
3381
3382void MacroAssembler::SubS32(Register dst, Register src, int32_t imm) {
3383 SubS32(dst, src, Operand(imm));
3384}
3385
3386// Subtract 32-bit (Register dst = Register src - Immediate opnd)
3387void MacroAssembler::SubS32(Register dst, Register src, const Operand& imm) {
3388 AddS32(dst, src, Operand(-(imm.immediate())));
3389}
3390
3391void MacroAssembler::SubS64(Register dst, Register src, int32_t imm) {
3392 SubS64(dst, src, Operand(imm));
3393}

3395// Subtract Pointer Sized (Register dst = Register src - Immediate opnd)
3396void MacroAssembler::SubS64(Register dst, Register src, const Operand& imm) {
3397 AddS64(dst, src, Operand(-(imm.immediate())));
3398}

3400// Subtract 32-bit (Register dst = Register dst - Register src)
3401void MacroAssembler::SubS32(Register dst, Register src) { sr(dst, src); }
3402
3403// Subtract Pointer Size (Register dst = Register dst - Register src)
3404void MacroAssembler::SubS64(Register dst, Register src) { sgr(dst, src); }
3405
3406// Subtract 32-bit (Register = Register - Register)
3407void MacroAssembler::SubS32(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3408 // Use non-clobbering version if possible
3409 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3410 srk(dst, src1, src2);
3411 return;
3412 }
3413 if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) lr(dst, src1);
3414 // In scenario where we have dst = src - dst, we need to swap and negate
3415 if (dst != src1 && dst == src2) {
3416 Label done;
3417 lcr(dst, dst); // dst = -dst
3418 b(overflow, &done);
3419 ar(dst, src1); // dst = dst + src
3420 bind(&done);
3421 } else {
3422 sr(dst, src2);
3423 }
3424}
3425
3426// Subtract Pointer Sized (Register = Register - Register)
3427void MacroAssembler::SubS64(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3428 // Use non-clobbering version if possible
3429 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3430 sgrk(dst, src1, src2);
3431 return;
3432 }
3433 if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) mov(dst, src1);
3434 // In scenario where we have dst = src - dst, we need to swap and negate
3435 if (dst != src1 && dst == src2) {
3436 Label done;
3437 lcgr(dst, dst); // dst = -dst
3438 b(overflow, &done);
3439 AddS64(dst, src1); // dst = dst + src
3440 bind(&done);
3441 } else {
3442 SubS64(dst, src2);
3443 }
3444}
3445
3446// Subtract 32-bit (Register-Memory)
3447void MacroAssembler::SubS32(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3448 DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3449 if (is_uint12(opnd.offset()))
3450 s(dst, opnd);
3451 else
3452 sy(dst, opnd);
3453}
3454
3455// Subtract Pointer Sized (Register - Memory)
3456void MacroAssembler::SubS64(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3457 sg(dst, opnd);
3458}

3460void MacroAssembler::MovIntToFloat(DoubleRegister dst, Register src) {
3461 sllg(r0, src, Operand(32));
3462 ldgr(dst, r0);
3463}
3464
3465void MacroAssembler::MovFloatToInt(Register dst, DoubleRegister src) {
3466 lgdr(dst, src);
3467 srlg(dst, dst, Operand(32));
3468}

3471void MacroAssembler::LoadAndSub32(Register dst, Register src,
3472 const MemOperand& opnd) {

3502//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3503// Bitwise Operations
3504//----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3505
3506// AND 32-bit - dst = dst & src
3507void MacroAssembler::And(Register dst, Register src) { nr(dst, src); }
3508
3509// AND Pointer Size - dst = dst & src
3510void MacroAssembler::AndP(Register dst, Register src) { ngr(dst, src); }
3511
3512// Non-clobbering AND 32-bit - dst = src1 & src1
3513void MacroAssembler::And(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3514 if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) {
3515 // We prefer to generate XR/XGR, over the non clobbering XRK/XRK
3516 // as XR is a smaller instruction
3517 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3518 nrk(dst, src1, src2);
3519 return;
3520 } else {
3521 lr(dst, src1);
3522 }
3523 } else if (dst == src2) {
3524 src2 = src1;
3525 }
3526 And(dst, src2);
3527}
3528
3529// Non-clobbering AND pointer size - dst = src1 & src1
3530void MacroAssembler::AndP(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3531 if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) {
3532 // We prefer to generate XR/XGR, over the non clobbering XRK/XRK
3533 // as XR is a smaller instruction
3534 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3535 ngrk(dst, src1, src2);
3536 return;
3537 } else {
3538 mov(dst, src1);
3539 }
3540 } else if (dst == src2) {
3541 src2 = src1;
3542 }
3543 AndP(dst, src2);
3544}
3545
3546// AND 32-bit (Reg - Mem)
3547void MacroAssembler::And(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3548 DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3549 if (is_uint12(opnd.offset()))
3550 n(dst, opnd);
3551 else
3552 ny(dst, opnd);
3553}
3554
3555// AND Pointer Size (Reg - Mem)
3556void MacroAssembler::AndP(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3557 DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3558 ng(dst, opnd);
3559}
3560
3561// AND 32-bit - dst = dst & imm
3562void MacroAssembler::And(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) { nilf(dst, opnd); }
3563
3564// AND Pointer Size - dst = dst & imm
3565void MacroAssembler::AndP(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) {
3566 intptr_t value = opnd.immediate();
3567 if (value >> 32 != -1) {
3568 // this may not work b/c condition code won't be set correctly
3569 nihf(dst, Operand(value >> 32));
3570 }
3571 nilf(dst, Operand(value & 0xFFFFFFFF));
3572}
3573
3574// AND 32-bit - dst = src & imm
3575void MacroAssembler::And(Register dst, Register src, const Operand& opnd) {
3576 if (dst != src) lr(dst, src);
3577 nilf(dst, opnd);
3578}
3579
3580// AND Pointer Size - dst = src & imm
3581void MacroAssembler::AndP(Register dst, Register src, const Operand& opnd) {
3582 // Try to exploit RISBG first
3583 intptr_t value = opnd.immediate();
3584 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(GENERAL_INSTR_EXT)) {
3585 intptr_t shifted_value = value;
3586 int trailing_zeros = 0;
3587
3588 // We start checking how many trailing zeros are left at the end.
3589 while ((0 != shifted_value) && (0 == (shifted_value & 1))) {
3590 trailing_zeros++;
3591 shifted_value >>= 1;
3592 }
3593
3594 // If temp (value with right-most set of zeros shifted out) is 1 less
3595 // than power of 2, we have consecutive bits of 1.
3596 // Special case: If shift_value is zero, we cannot use RISBG, as it requires
3597 // selection of at least 1 bit.
3598 if ((0 != shifted_value) && base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(shifted_value + 1)) {
3599 int startBit =
3600 base::bits::CountLeadingZeros64(shifted_value) - trailing_zeros;
3601 int endBit = 63 - trailing_zeros;
3602 // Start: startBit, End: endBit, Shift = 0, true = zero unselected bits.
3603 RotateInsertSelectBits(dst, src, Operand(startBit), Operand(endBit),
3604 Operand::Zero(), true);
3605 return;
3606 } else if (-1 == shifted_value) {
3607 // A Special case in which all top bits up to MSB are 1's. In this case,
3608 // we can set startBit to be 0.
3609 int endBit = 63 - trailing_zeros;
3610 RotateInsertSelectBits(dst, src, Operand::Zero(), Operand(endBit),
3611 Operand::Zero(), true);
3612 return;
3613 }
3614 }
3615
3616 // If we are &'ing zero, we can just whack the dst register and skip copy
3617 if (dst != src && (0 != value)) mov(dst, src);
3618 AndP(dst, opnd);
3619}
3620
3621// OR 32-bit - dst = dst & src
3622void MacroAssembler::Or(Register dst, Register src) { or_z(dst, src); }
3623
3624// OR Pointer Size - dst = dst & src
3625void MacroAssembler::OrP(Register dst, Register src) { ogr(dst, src); }
3626
3627// Non-clobbering OR 32-bit - dst = src1 & src1
3628void MacroAssembler::Or(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3629 if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) {
3630 // We prefer to generate XR/XGR, over the non clobbering XRK/XRK
3631 // as XR is a smaller instruction
3632 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3633 ork(dst, src1, src2);
3634 return;
3635 } else {
3636 lr(dst, src1);
3637 }
3638 } else if (dst == src2) {
3639 src2 = src1;
3640 }
3641 Or(dst, src2);
3642}
3643
3644// Non-clobbering OR pointer size - dst = src1 & src1
3645void MacroAssembler::OrP(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3646 if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) {
3647 // We prefer to generate XR/XGR, over the non clobbering XRK/XRK
3648 // as XR is a smaller instruction
3649 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3650 ogrk(dst, src1, src2);
3651 return;
3652 } else {
3653 mov(dst, src1);
3654 }
3655 } else if (dst == src2) {
3656 src2 = src1;
3657 }
3658 OrP(dst, src2);
3659}

3667 oy(dst, opnd);

3674}

3677void MacroAssembler::Or(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) { oilf(dst, opnd); }
3678

3687}

3802//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3803// Compare Helpers
3804//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3805
3806// Compare 32-bit Register vs Register
3807void MacroAssembler::CmpS32(Register src1, Register src2) { cr_z(src1, src2); }
3808
3809// Compare Pointer Sized Register vs Register
3810void MacroAssembler::CmpS64(Register src1, Register src2) { cgr(src1, src2); }
3811
3812// Compare 32-bit Register vs Immediate
3813// This helper will set up proper relocation entries if required.
3814void MacroAssembler::CmpS32(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) {
3815 if (opnd.rmode() == RelocInfo::NO_INFO) {
3816 intptr_t value = opnd.immediate();
3817 if (is_int16(value))
3818 chi(dst, opnd);
3819 else
3820 cfi(dst, opnd);
3821 } else {
3822 // Need to generate relocation record here
3823 RecordRelocInfo(opnd.rmode(), opnd.immediate());
3824 cfi(dst, opnd);
3825 }
3826}
3827
3828// Compare Pointer Sized Register vs Immediate
3829// This helper will set up proper relocation entries if required.
3830void MacroAssembler::CmpS64(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) {
3831 if (opnd.rmode() == RelocInfo::NO_INFO) {
3832 cgfi(dst, opnd);
3833 } else {
3834 mov(r0, opnd); // Need to generate 64-bit relocation
3835 cgr(dst, r0);
3836 }
3837}
3838
3839// Compare 32-bit Register vs Memory
3840void MacroAssembler::CmpS32(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3841 // make sure offset is within 20 bit range
3842 DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3843 if (is_uint12(opnd.offset()))
3844 c(dst, opnd);
3845 else
3846 cy(dst, opnd);
3847}
3848
3849// Compare Pointer Size Register vs Memory
3850void MacroAssembler::CmpS64(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3851 // make sure offset is within 20 bit range
3852 DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3853 cg(dst, opnd);
3854}
3855
3856void MacroAssembler::CmpF32(DoubleRegister src1, DoubleRegister src2) {
3857 cebr(src1, src2);
3858}
3859
3860void MacroAssembler::CmpF64(DoubleRegister src1, DoubleRegister src2) {
3861 cdbr(src1, src2);
3862}
3863
3864void MacroAssembler::CmpF32(DoubleRegister src1, const MemOperand& src2) {
3865 DCHECK(is_int12(src2.offset()));
3866 ceb(src1, src2);
3867}
3868
3869void MacroAssembler::CmpF64(DoubleRegister src1, const MemOperand& src2) {
3870 DCHECK(is_int12(src2.offset()));
3871 cdb(src1, src2);
3872}
3873
3874// Using cs or scy based on the offset
3875void MacroAssembler::CmpAndSwap(Register old_val, Register new_val,
3876 const MemOperand& opnd) {
3877 if (is_uint12(opnd.offset())) {
3878 cs(old_val, new_val, opnd);
3879 } else {
3880 csy(old_val, new_val, opnd);
3881 }
3882}
3883
3884void MacroAssembler::CmpAndSwap64(Register old_val, Register new_val,
3885 const MemOperand& opnd) {
3886 DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3887 csg(old_val, new_val, opnd);
3888}

3890//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3891// Compare Logical Helpers
3892//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
3893
3894// Compare Logical 32-bit Register vs Register
3895void MacroAssembler::CmpU32(Register dst, Register src) { clr(dst, src); }
3896
3897// Compare Logical Pointer Sized Register vs Register
3898void MacroAssembler::CmpU64(Register dst, Register src) {
3899 clgr(dst, src);
3900}
3901
3902// Compare Logical 32-bit Register vs Immediate
3903void MacroAssembler::CmpU32(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) {
3904 clfi(dst, opnd);
3905}
3906
3907// Compare Logical Pointer Sized Register vs Immediate
3908void MacroAssembler::CmpU64(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) {
3909 DCHECK_EQ(static_cast<uint32_t>(opnd.immediate() >> 32), 0);
3910 clgfi(dst, opnd);
3911}
3912
3913// Compare Logical 32-bit Register vs Memory
3914void MacroAssembler::CmpU32(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3915 // make sure offset is within 20 bit range
3916 DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3917 if (is_uint12(opnd.offset()))
3918 cl(dst, opnd);
3919 else
3920 cly(dst, opnd);
3921}
3922
3923// Compare Logical Pointer Sized Register vs Memory
3924void MacroAssembler::CmpU64(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3925 // make sure offset is within 20 bit range
3926 DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3927 clg(dst, opnd);
3928}
3929
3930void MacroAssembler::Branch(Condition c, const Operand& opnd) {
3931 intptr_t value = opnd.immediate();
3932 if (is_int16(value))
3933 brc(c, opnd);
3934 else
3935 brcl(c, opnd);
3936}
3937
3938// Branch On Count. Decrement R1, and branch if R1 != 0.
3939void MacroAssembler::BranchOnCount(Register r1, Label* l) {
3940 int32_t offset = branch_offset(l);
3941 if (is_int16(offset)) {
3942 brctg(r1, Operand(offset));
3943 } else {
3944 AddS64(r1, Operand(-1));
3945 Branch(ne, Operand(offset));
3946 }
3947}
3948
3949void MacroAssembler::LoadSmiLiteral(Register dst, Tagged<Smi> smi) {
3950 intptr_t value = static_cast<intptr_t>(smi.ptr());
3951#if defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS) || defined(V8_31BIT_SMIS_ON_64BIT_ARCH)
3952 llilf(dst, Operand(value));
3953#else
3954 DCHECK_EQ(value & 0xFFFFFFFF, 0);
3955 // The smi value is loaded in upper 32-bits. Lower 32-bit are zeros.
3956 llihf(dst, Operand(value >> 32));
3957#endif
3958}
3959
3960void MacroAssembler::CmpSmiLiteral(Register src1, Tagged<Smi> smi,
3961 Register scratch) {
3962#if defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS) || defined(V8_31BIT_SMIS_ON_64BIT_ARCH)
3963 // CFI takes 32-bit immediate.
3964 cfi(src1, Operand(smi));
3965#else
3966 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3967 cih(src1, Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(smi.ptr()) >> 32));
3968 } else {
3969 LoadSmiLiteral(scratch, smi);
3970 cgr(src1, scratch);
3971 }
3972#endif
3973}
3974
3975void MacroAssembler::LoadU64(Register dst, const MemOperand& mem,
3976 Register scratch) {
3977 int offset = mem.offset();
3978
3979 MemOperand src = mem;
3980 if (!is_int20(offset)) {
3981 DCHECK(scratch != no_reg && scratch != r0 && mem.rx() == r0);
3982 DCHECK(scratch != mem.rb());
3983 mov(scratch, Operand(offset));
3984 src = MemOperand(mem.rb(), scratch);
3985 }
3986 lg(dst, src);
3987}
3988
3989// Store a "pointer" sized value to the memory location
3990void MacroAssembler::StoreU64(Register src, const MemOperand& mem,
3991 Register scratch) {
3992 if (!is_int20(mem.offset())) {
3993 DCHECK(scratch != no_reg);
3994 DCHECK(scratch != r0);
3995 mov(scratch, Operand(mem.offset()));
3996 stg(src, MemOperand(mem.rb(), scratch));
3997 } else {
3998 stg(src, mem);
3999 }
4000}
4001
4002// Store a "pointer" sized constant to the memory location
4003void MacroAssembler::StoreU64(const MemOperand& mem, const Operand& opnd,
4004 Register scratch) {
4005 // Relocations not supported
4006 DCHECK_EQ(opnd.rmode(), RelocInfo::NO_INFO);
4007
4008 // Try to use MVGHI/MVHI
4009 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(GENERAL_INSTR_EXT) && is_uint12(mem.offset()) &&
4010 mem.getIndexRegister() == r0 && is_int16(opnd.immediate())) {
4011 mvghi(mem, opnd);
4012 } else {
4013 mov(scratch, opnd);
4014 StoreU64(scratch, mem);
4015 }
4016}

4021 lmg(dst1, dst2, mem);

4055// Load 32-bits and sign extend if necessary.
4056void MacroAssembler::LoadS32(Register dst, const MemOperand& mem,
4057 Register scratch) {
4058 int offset = mem.offset();
4059
4060 if (!is_int20(offset)) {
4061 DCHECK(scratch != no_reg);
4062 mov(scratch, Operand(offset));
4063 lgf(dst, MemOperand(mem.rb(), scratch));
4064 } else {
4065 lgf(dst, mem);
4066 }

4069// Load 32-bits and zero extend if necessary.
4070void MacroAssembler::LoadU32(Register dst, Register src) {
4071 llgfr(dst, src);
4072}
4073
4074// Variable length depending on whether offset fits into immediate field
4075// MemOperand of RX or RXY format
4076void MacroAssembler::LoadU32(Register dst, const MemOperand& mem,
4077 Register scratch) {
4078 Register base = mem.rb();
4079 int offset = mem.offset();
4080
4081 if (is_int20(offset)) {
4082 llgf(dst, mem);
4083 } else if (scratch != no_reg) {
4084 // Materialize offset into scratch register.
4085 mov(scratch, Operand(offset));
4086 llgf(dst, MemOperand(base, scratch));
4087 } else {
4088 DCHECK(false);
4089 }
4090}

4234 strvg(scratch1, mem);
4235 strvg(scratch2,
4236 MemOperand(mem.rx(), mem.rb(), mem.offset() + kSystemPointerSize));

4402void MacroAssembler::AddF32(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
4403 DoubleRegister rhs) {
4404 if (dst == lhs) {
4405 aebr(dst, rhs);
4406 } else if (dst == rhs) {
4407 aebr(dst, lhs);
4408 } else {
4409 ler(dst, lhs);
4410 aebr(dst, rhs);
4411 }
4412}

4415 DoubleRegister rhs) {
4416 if (dst == lhs) {
4417 sebr(dst, rhs);
4418 } else if (dst == rhs) {
4419 sebr(dst, lhs);
4420 lcebr(dst, dst);
4421 } else {
4422 ler(dst, lhs);
4423 sebr(dst, rhs);
4424 }
4425}

4428 DoubleRegister rhs) {
4429 if (dst == lhs) {
4430 meebr(dst, rhs);
4431 } else if (dst == rhs) {
4432 meebr(dst, lhs);
4433 } else {
4434 ler(dst, lhs);
4435 meebr(dst, rhs);

4439void MacroAssembler::DivF32(DoubleRegister dst, DoubleRegister lhs,
4440 DoubleRegister rhs) {
4441 if (dst == lhs) {
4442 debr(dst, rhs);
4443 } else if (dst == rhs) {
4444 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kSystemPointerSize));
4445 StoreF32(dst, MemOperand(sp));
4446 ler(dst, lhs);
4447 deb(dst, MemOperand(sp));
4448 la(sp, MemOperand(sp, kSystemPointerSize));
4449 } else {
4450 ler(dst, lhs);
4451 debr(dst, rhs);
4452 }
4453}

4457 if (dst == lhs) {
4458 adbr(dst, rhs);
4459 } else if (dst == rhs) {
4460 adbr(dst, lhs);
4461 } else {
4462 ldr(dst, lhs);
4463 adbr(dst, rhs);
4464 }
4465}

4596
4597// Variable length depending on whether offset fits into immediate field
4598// MemOperand of RX or RXY format
4599void MacroAssembler::StoreU32(Register src, const MemOperand& mem,
4600 Register scratch) {
4601 Register base = mem.rb();
4602 int offset = mem.offset();
4603
4604 bool use_RXform = false;
4605 bool use_RXYform = false;
4606
4607 if (is_uint12(offset)) {
4608 // RX-format supports unsigned 12-bits offset.
4609 use_RXform = true;
4610 } else if (is_int20(offset)) {
4611 // RXY-format supports signed 20-bits offset.
4612 use_RXYform = true;
4613 } else if (scratch != no_reg) {
4614 // Materialize offset into scratch register.
4615 mov(scratch, Operand(offset));
4616 } else {
4617 // scratch is no_reg
4618 DCHECK(false);
4619 }
4620
4621 if (use_RXform) {
4622 st(src, mem);
4623 } else if (use_RXYform) {
4624 sty(src, mem);
4625 } else {
4626 StoreU32(src, MemOperand(base, scratch));
4627 }
4628}
4629
4630void MacroAssembler::LoadS16(Register dst, Register src) {
4631 lghr(dst, src);
4632}
4633
4634// Loads 16-bits half-word value from memory and sign extends to pointer
4635// sized register
4636void MacroAssembler::LoadS16(Register dst, const MemOperand& mem,
4637 Register scratch) {
4638 Register base = mem.rb();
4639 int offset = mem.offset();
4640
4641 if (!is_int20(offset)) {
4642 DCHECK(scratch != no_reg);
4643 mov(scratch, Operand(offset));
4644 lgh(dst, MemOperand(base, scratch));
4645 } else {
4646 lgh(dst, mem);
4647 }
4648}
4649
4650// Variable length depending on whether offset fits into immediate field
4651// MemOperand current only supports d-form
4652void MacroAssembler::StoreU16(Register src, const MemOperand& mem,
4653 Register scratch) {
4654 Register base = mem.rb();
4655 int offset = mem.offset();
4656
4657 if (is_uint12(offset)) {
4658 sth(src, mem);
4659 } else if (is_int20(offset)) {
4660 sthy(src, mem);
4661 } else {
4662 DCHECK(scratch != no_reg);
4663 mov(scratch, Operand(offset));
4664 sth(src, MemOperand(base, scratch));
4665 }
4666}
4667
4668// Variable length depending on whether offset fits into immediate field
4669// MemOperand current only supports d-form
4670void MacroAssembler::StoreU8(Register src, const MemOperand& mem,
4671 Register scratch) {
4672 Register base = mem.rb();
4673 int offset = mem.offset();
4674
4675 if (is_uint12(offset)) {
4676 stc(src, mem);
4677 } else if (is_int20(offset)) {
4678 stcy(src, mem);
4679 } else {
4680 DCHECK(scratch != no_reg);
4681 mov(scratch, Operand(offset));
4682 stc(src, MemOperand(base, scratch));
4683 }
4684}
4685
4686// Shift left logical for 32-bit integer types.
4687void MacroAssembler::ShiftLeftU32(Register dst, Register src,
4688 const Operand& val) {
4689 ShiftLeftU32(dst, src, r0, val);
4690}
4691
4692// Shift left logical for 32-bit integer types.
4693void MacroAssembler::ShiftLeftU32(Register dst, Register src, Register val,
4694 const Operand& val2) {
4695 if (dst == src) {
4696 sll(dst, val, val2);
4697 } else if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
4698 sllk(dst, src, val, val2);
4699 } else {
4700 DCHECK(dst != val || val == r0); // The lr/sll path clobbers val.
4701 lr(dst, src);
4702 sll(dst, val, val2);
4703 }
4704}
4705
4706// Shift left logical for 32-bit integer types.
4707void MacroAssembler::ShiftLeftU64(Register dst, Register src,
4708 const Operand& val) {
4709 ShiftLeftU64(dst, src, r0, val);
4710}
4711
4712// Shift left logical for 32-bit integer types.
4713void MacroAssembler::ShiftLeftU64(Register dst, Register src, Register val,
4714 const Operand& val2) {
4715 sllg(dst, src, val, val2);
4716}

4718// Shift right logical for 32-bit integer types.
4719void MacroAssembler::ShiftRightU32(Register dst, Register src,
4720 const Operand& val) {

4723

4725void MacroAssembler::ShiftRightU32(Register dst, Register src, Register val,

4727 if (dst == src) {
4728 srl(dst, val, val2);
4729 } else if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
4730 srlk(dst, src, val, val2);
4731 } else {
4732 DCHECK(dst != val || val == r0); // The lr/srl path clobbers val.
4733 lr(dst, src);
4734 srl(dst, val, val2);
4735 }
4736}

4756void MacroAssembler::ShiftRightS32(Register dst, Register src, Register val,
4757 const Operand& val2) {
4758 if (dst == src) {
4759 sra(dst, val, val2);
4760 } else if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
4761 srak(dst, src, val, val2);
4762 } else {

4764 lr(dst, src);

4766 }

4780
4781// Clear right most # of bits
4782void MacroAssembler::ClearRightImm(Register dst, Register src,
4783 const Operand& val) {
4784 int numBitsToClear = val.immediate() % (kSystemPointerSize * 8);
4785
4786 // Try to use RISBG if possible
4787 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(GENERAL_INSTR_EXT)) {
4788 int endBit = 63 - numBitsToClear;
4789 RotateInsertSelectBits(dst, src, Operand::Zero(), Operand(endBit),
4790 Operand::Zero(), true);
4791 return;
4792 }
4793
4794 uint64_t hexMask = ~((1L << numBitsToClear) - 1);
4795
4796 // S390 AND instr clobbers source. Make a copy if necessary
4797 if (dst != src) mov(dst, src);
4798
4799 if (numBitsToClear <= 16) {
4800 nill(dst, Operand(static_cast<uint16_t>(hexMask)));
4801 } else if (numBitsToClear <= 32) {
4802 nilf(dst, Operand(static_cast<uint32_t>(hexMask)));
4803 } else if (numBitsToClear <= 64) {
4804 nilf(dst, Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(0)));
4805 nihf(dst, Operand(hexMask >> 32));
4806 }
4807}
4808
4809void MacroAssembler::Popcnt32(Register dst, Register src) {
4810 DCHECK(src != r0);
4811 DCHECK(dst != r0);
4812
4813 popcnt(dst, src);
4814 ShiftRightU32(r0, dst, Operand(16));
4815 ar(dst, r0);
4816 ShiftRightU32(r0, dst, Operand(8));
4817 ar(dst, r0);
4818 llgcr(dst, dst);
4819}
4820
4821void MacroAssembler::Popcnt64(Register dst, Register src) {
4822 DCHECK(src != r0);
4823 DCHECK(dst != r0);
4824
4825 popcnt(dst, src);
4826 ShiftRightU64(r0, dst, Operand(32));
4827 AddS64(dst, r0);
4828 ShiftRightU64(r0, dst, Operand(16));
4829 AddS64(dst, r0);
4830 ShiftRightU64(r0, dst, Operand(8));
4831 AddS64(dst, r0);
4832 LoadU8(dst, dst);
4833}

4835void MacroAssembler::SwapP(Register src, Register dst, Register scratch) {
4836 if (src == dst) return;
4837 DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst, scratch));
4838 mov(scratch, src);
4839 mov(src, dst);
4840 mov(dst, scratch);
4841}
4842
4843void MacroAssembler::SwapP(Register src, MemOperand dst, Register scratch) {
4844 if (dst.rx() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst.rx(), scratch));
4845 if (dst.rb() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst.rb(), scratch));
4846 DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, scratch));
4847 mov(scratch, src);
4848 LoadU64(src, dst);
4849 StoreU64(scratch, dst);
4850}
4851
4852void MacroAssembler::SwapP(MemOperand src, MemOperand dst, Register scratch_0,
4853 Register scratch_1) {
4854 if (src.rx() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(src.rx(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
4855 if (src.rb() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(src.rb(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
4856 if (dst.rx() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst.rx(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
4857 if (dst.rb() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst.rb(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
4858 DCHECK(!AreAliased(scratch_0, scratch_1));
4859 LoadU64(scratch_0, src);
4860 LoadU64(scratch_1, dst);
4861 StoreU64(scratch_0, dst);
4862 StoreU64(scratch_1, src);
4863}

4865void MacroAssembler::SwapFloat32(DoubleRegister src, DoubleRegister dst,
4866 DoubleRegister scratch) {
4867 if (src == dst) return;
4868 DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst, scratch));
4869 ldr(scratch, src);
4870 ldr(src, dst);
4871 ldr(dst, scratch);
4872}
4873
4874void MacroAssembler::SwapFloat32(DoubleRegister src, MemOperand dst,
4875 DoubleRegister scratch) {
4876 DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, scratch));
4877 ldr(scratch, src);
4878 LoadF32(src, dst);
4879 StoreF32(scratch, dst);
4880}
4881
4882void MacroAssembler::SwapFloat32(MemOperand src, MemOperand dst,
4883 DoubleRegister scratch) {
4884 // push d0, to be used as scratch
4885 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kDoubleSize));
4886 StoreF64(d0, MemOperand(sp));
4887 LoadF32(scratch, src);
4888 LoadF32(d0, dst);
4889 StoreF32(scratch, dst);
4890 StoreF32(d0, src);
4891 // restore d0
4892 LoadF64(d0, MemOperand(sp));
4893 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, kDoubleSize));
4894}

4898 if (src == dst) return;
4899 DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst, scratch));
4900 ldr(scratch, src);
4901 ldr(src, dst);
4902 ldr(dst, scratch);
4903}

4908 ldr(scratch, src);
4909 LoadF64(src, dst);
4910 StoreF64(scratch, dst);
4911}

4913void MacroAssembler::SwapDouble(MemOperand src, MemOperand dst,

4916 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kDoubleSize));
4917 StoreF64(d0, MemOperand(sp));
4918 LoadF64(scratch, src);
4919 LoadF64(d0, dst);
4920 StoreF64(scratch, dst);
4921 StoreF64(d0, src);
4922 // restore d0
4923 LoadF64(d0, MemOperand(sp));
4924 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, kDoubleSize));
4925}

4929 if (src == dst) return;
4930 vlr(scratch, src, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));
4931 vlr(src, dst, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));
4932 vlr(dst, scratch, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));

4949 LoadV128(d0, dst, ip);
4950 StoreV128(scratch, dst, ip);
4951 StoreV128(d0, src, ip);

4954 lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, kSimd128Size));
4955}

4976
4977void MacroAssembler::LoadEntryFromBuiltinIndex(Register builtin_index,
4978 Register target) {
4979 static_assert(kSystemPointerSize == 8);
4980 static_assert(kSmiTagSize == 1);
4981 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
4982 // The builtin_index register contains the builtin index as a Smi.
4983 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
4984 ShiftRightS64(target, builtin_index,
4985 Operand(kSmiShift - kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
4986 } else {
4987 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
4988 ShiftLeftU64(target, builtin_index,
4989 Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2 - kSmiShift));
4990 }
4991 LoadU64(target, MemOperand(kRootRegister, target,
4992 IsolateData::builtin_entry_table_offset()));
4993}
4994
4995void MacroAssembler::CallBuiltinByIndex(Register builtin_index,
4996 Register target) {
4997 LoadEntryFromBuiltinIndex(builtin_index, target);
4998 Call(target);
4999}

5001void MacroAssembler::LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Builtin builtin,
5002 Register destination) {
5003 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5004 LoadU64(destination, EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(builtin));
5005}
5006
5007MemOperand MacroAssembler::EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(Builtin builtin) {
5008 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5009 DCHECK(root_array_available());
5010 return MemOperand(kRootRegister,
5011 IsolateData::BuiltinEntrySlotOffset(builtin));
5012}

5014#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5015
5016void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(Register destination,
5017 Register dispatch_handle,
5018 Register scratch) {
5019 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, dispatch_handle, scratch));
5020 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5021
5022 Register index = destination;
5023 Move(scratch, ExternalReference::js_dispatch_table_address());
5024 ShiftRightU64(index, dispatch_handle, Operand(kJSDispatchHandleShift));
5025 ShiftLeftU64(index, index, Operand(kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2));
5026 AddS64(scratch, scratch, index);
5027 LoadU64(destination, MemOperand(scratch, JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset));
5028}
5029
5030#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING

5033 Register code_object,
5034 CodeEntrypointTag tag) {
5035 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5036 LoadU64(destination,
5037 FieldMemOperand(code_object, Code::kInstructionStartOffset));
5038}

5040void MacroAssembler::CallCodeObject(Register code_object) {

5042 LoadCodeInstructionStart(code_object, code_object);
5043 Call(code_object);
5044}

5046void MacroAssembler::JumpCodeObject(Register code_object, JumpMode jump_mode) {
5047 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5048 DCHECK_EQ(JumpMode::kJump, jump_mode);
5049 LoadCodeInstructionStart(code_object, code_object);
5050 Jump(code_object);
5051}
5052
5053void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object,
5054 uint16_t argument_count) {
5055 Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
5056#if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5057 Register dispatch_handle = r0;
5058 Register scratch = ip;
5059 LoadU32(dispatch_handle,
5060 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
5061 LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle, scratch);
5062 Call(code);
5063#else
5064 LoadTaggedField(code,
5065 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
5066 CallCodeObject(code);
5067#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5068}
5069
5070#if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5071void MacroAssembler::CallJSDispatchEntry(JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
5072 uint16_t argument_count) {
5073 Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
5074 Register dispatch_handle_reg = r0;
5075 Register scratch = ip;
5076 mov(dispatch_handle_reg,
5077 Operand(dispatch_handle.value(), RelocInfo::JS_DISPATCH_HANDLE));
5078 // WARNING: This entrypoint load is only safe because we are storing a
5079 // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle in the movl above (thus keeping the
5080 // dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not compactable
5081 // (thus meaning that the calculation in the entrypoint load is not
5082 // invalidated by a compaction).
5083 // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
5084 static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
5085 LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle_reg, scratch);
5086 CHECK_EQ(argument_count,
5087 IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->GetParameterCount(
5088 dispatch_handle));
5089 Call(code);
5090}
5091#endif
5092
5093void MacroAssembler::JumpJSFunction(Register function_object,
5094 JumpMode jump_mode) {
5095 Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
5096#if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5097 Register dispatch_handle = r0;
5098 Register scratch = ip;
5099 LoadU32(dispatch_handle,
5100 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
5101 LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle, scratch);
5102 Jump(code);
5103#else
5104 LoadTaggedField(code,
5105 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
5106 JumpCodeObject(code, jump_mode);
5107#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5108}
5109
5110#if V8_OS_ZOS
5111// Helper for CallApiFunctionAndReturn().
5112void MacroAssembler::zosStoreReturnAddressAndCall(Register target,
5113 Register scratch) {
5114 DCHECK(target == r3 || target == r4);
5115 // Shuffle the arguments from Linux arg register to XPLINK arg regs
5116 mov(r1, r2);
5117 if (target == r3) {
5118 mov(r2, r3);
5119 } else {
5120 mov(r2, r3);
5121 mov(r3, r4);
5122 }
5123
5124 // Update System Stack Pointer with the appropriate XPLINK stack bias.
5125 lay(r4, MemOperand(sp, -kStackPointerBias));
5126
5127 // Preserve r7 by placing into callee-saved register r13
5128 mov(r13, r7);
5129
5130 // Load function pointer from slot 1 of fn desc.
5131 LoadU64(ip, MemOperand(scratch, kSystemPointerSize));
5132 // Load environment from slot 0 of fn desc.
5133 LoadU64(r5, MemOperand(scratch));
5134
5135 StoreReturnAddressAndCall(ip);
5136
5137 // Restore r7 from r13
5138 mov(r7, r13);
5139}
5140#endif // V8_OS_ZOS
5141
5142#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5143
5144void MacroAssembler::ResolveWasmCodePointer(Register target) {
5145 static_assert(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
5146 ExternalReference global_jump_table =
5147 ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
5148 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5149 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5150 Move(scratch, global_jump_table);
5151 static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == kSystemPointerSize);
5152 ShiftLeftU32(target, target, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
5153 LoadU64(target, MemOperand(scratch, target));
5154}
5155
5156void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointer(Register target,
5157 CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
5158 ResolveWasmCodePointer(target);
5159 if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
5160 Jump(target);
5161 } else {
5162 Call(target);
5163 }
5164}
5165
5166void MacroAssembler::LoadWasmCodePointer(Register dst, MemOperand src) {
5167 static_assert(sizeof(WasmCodePointer) == 4);
5168 LoadU32(dst, src);
5169}
5170
5171#endif
5172
5173void MacroAssembler::StoreReturnAddressAndCall(Register target) {
5174 // This generates the final instruction sequence for calls to C functions
5175 // once an exit frame has been constructed.
5176 //
5177 // Note that this assumes the caller code (i.e. the InstructionStream object
5178 // currently being generated) is immovable or that the callee function cannot
5179 // trigger GC, since the callee function will return to it.
5180
5181#if V8_OS_ZOS
5182 Register ra = r7;
5183#else
5184 Register ra = r14;
5185#endif
5186 Label return_label;
5187 larl(ra, &return_label); // Generate the return addr of call later.
5188#if V8_OS_ZOS
5189 // Mimic the XPLINK expected no-op (2-byte) instruction at the return point.
5190 // When the C call returns, the 2 bytes are skipped and then the proper
5191 // instruction is executed.
5192 lay(ra, MemOperand(ra, -2));
5193#endif
5194 StoreU64(ra, MemOperand(sp, kStackFrameRASlot * kSystemPointerSize));
5195
5196 // zLinux ABI requires caller's frame to have sufficient space for callee
5197 // preserved regsiter save area.
5198 b(target);
5199 bind(&return_label);
5200}
5201
5202// Check if the code object is marked for deoptimization. If it is, then it
5203// jumps to the CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode builtin. In order to do this we need
5204// to:
5205// 1. read from memory the word that contains that bit, which can be found in
5206// the flags in the referenced {Code} object;
5207// 2. test kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit in those flags; and
5208// 3. if it is not zero then it jumps to the builtin.
5209//
5210// Note: With leaptiering we simply assert the code is not deoptimized.
5211void MacroAssembler::BailoutIfDeoptimized(Register scratch) {
5212 int offset = InstructionStream::kCodeOffset - InstructionStream::kHeaderSize;
5213 if (v8_flags.debug_code || !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL) {
5214 LoadTaggedField(scratch,
5215 MemOperand(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, offset));
5216 TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(scratch, scratch);
5217 }
5218#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5219 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5220 Assert(kZero, AbortReason::kInvalidDeoptimizedCode);
5221 }
5222#else
5223 Jump(BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode),
5224 RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET, ne);
5225#endif
5226}
5227
5228void MacroAssembler::CallForDeoptimization(Builtin target, int, Label* exit,
5229 DeoptimizeKind kind, Label* ret,
5230 Label*) {
5231 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5232 LoadU64(ip, MemOperand(kRootRegister,
5233 IsolateData::BuiltinEntrySlotOffset(target)));
5234 Call(ip);
5235 DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(exit),
5236 (kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy) ? Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize
5237 : Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
5238}
5239
5240void MacroAssembler::Trap() { stop(); }
5241void MacroAssembler::DebugBreak() { stop(); }
5242
5243void MacroAssembler::CountLeadingZerosU32(Register dst, Register src,
5244 Register scratch_pair) {
5245 llgfr(dst, src);
5246 flogr(scratch_pair,
5247 dst); // will modify a register pair scratch and scratch + 1
5248 AddS32(dst, scratch_pair, Operand(-32));
5249}
5250
5251void MacroAssembler::CountLeadingZerosU64(Register dst, Register src,
5252 Register scratch_pair) {
5253 flogr(scratch_pair,
5254 src); // will modify a register pair scratch and scratch + 1
5255 mov(dst, scratch_pair);
5256}
5257
5258void MacroAssembler::CountTrailingZerosU32(Register dst, Register src,
5259 Register scratch_pair) {
5260 Register scratch0 = scratch_pair;
5261 Register scratch1 = Register::from_code(scratch_pair.code() + 1);
5262 DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst, scratch0, scratch1));
5263 DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, scratch0, scratch1));
5264
5265 Label done;
5266 // Check if src is all zeros.
5267 ltr(scratch1, src);
5268 mov(dst, Operand(32));
5269 beq(&done);
5270 llgfr(scratch1, scratch1);
5271 lcgr(scratch0, scratch1);
5272 ngr(scratch1, scratch0);
5273 flogr(scratch0, scratch1);
5274 mov(dst, Operand(63));
5275 SubS64(dst, scratch0);
5276 bind(&done);
5277}
5278
5279void MacroAssembler::CountTrailingZerosU64(Register dst, Register src,
5280 Register scratch_pair) {
5281 Register scratch0 = scratch_pair;
5282 Register scratch1 = Register::from_code(scratch_pair.code() + 1);
5283 DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst, scratch0, scratch1));
5284 DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, scratch0, scratch1));
5285
5286 Label done;
5287 // Check if src is all zeros.
5288 ltgr(scratch1, src);
5289 mov(dst, Operand(64));
5290 beq(&done);
5291 lcgr(scratch0, scratch1);
5292 ngr(scratch0, scratch1);
5293 flogr(scratch0, scratch0);
5294 mov(dst, Operand(63));
5295 SubS64(dst, scratch0);
5296 bind(&done);
5297}
5298
5299void MacroAssembler::AtomicCmpExchangeHelper(Register addr, Register output,
5300 Register old_value,
5301 Register new_value, int start,
5302 int end, int shift_amount,
5303 int offset, Register temp0,
5304 Register temp1) {
5305 LoadU32(temp0, MemOperand(addr, offset));
5306 llgfr(temp1, temp0);
5307 RotateInsertSelectBits(temp0, old_value, Operand(start), Operand(end),
5308 Operand(shift_amount), false);
5309 RotateInsertSelectBits(temp1, new_value, Operand(start), Operand(end),
5310 Operand(shift_amount), false);
5311 CmpAndSwap(temp0, temp1, MemOperand(addr, offset));
5312 RotateInsertSelectBits(output, temp0, Operand(start + shift_amount),
5313 Operand(end + shift_amount),
5314 Operand(64 - shift_amount), true);
5315}
5316
5317void MacroAssembler::AtomicCmpExchangeU8(Register addr, Register output,
5318 Register old_value, Register new_value,
5319 Register temp0, Register temp1) {
5320#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
5321#define ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(i) \
5322 { \
5323 constexpr int idx = (i); \
5324 static_assert(idx <= 3 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5325 constexpr int start = 32 + 8 * idx; \
5326 constexpr int end = start + 7; \
5327 constexpr int shift_amount = (3 - idx) * 8; \
5328 AtomicCmpExchangeHelper(addr, output, old_value, new_value, start, end, \
5329 shift_amount, -idx, temp0, temp1); \
5330 }
5331#else
5332#define ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(i) \
5333 { \
5334 constexpr int idx = (i); \
5335 static_assert(idx <= 3 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5336 constexpr int start = 32 + 8 * (3 - idx); \
5337 constexpr int end = start + 7; \
5338 constexpr int shift_amount = idx * 8; \
5339 AtomicCmpExchangeHelper(addr, output, old_value, new_value, start, end, \
5340 shift_amount, -idx, temp0, temp1); \
5341 }
5342#endif
5343
5344 Label one, two, three, done;
5345 tmll(addr, Operand(3));
5346 b(Condition(1), &three);
5347 b(Condition(2), &two);
5348 b(Condition(4), &one);
5349 /* ending with 0b00 */
5350 ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(0);
5351 b(&done);
5352 /* ending with 0b01 */
5353 bind(&one);
5354 ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(1);
5355 b(&done);
5356 /* ending with 0b10 */
5357 bind(&two);
5358 ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(2);
5359 b(&done);
5360 /* ending with 0b11 */
5361 bind(&three);
5362 ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(3);
5363 bind(&done);
5364}
5365
5366void MacroAssembler::AtomicCmpExchangeU16(Register addr, Register output,
5367 Register old_value,
5368 Register new_value, Register temp0,
5369 Register temp1) {
5370#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
5371#define ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(i) \
5372 { \
5373 constexpr int idx = (i); \
5374 static_assert(idx <= 1 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5375 constexpr int start = 32 + 16 * idx; \
5376 constexpr int end = start + 15; \
5377 constexpr int shift_amount = (1 - idx) * 16; \
5378 AtomicCmpExchangeHelper(addr, output, old_value, new_value, start, end, \
5379 shift_amount, -idx * 2, temp0, temp1); \
5380 }
5381#else
5382#define ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(i) \
5383 { \
5384 constexpr int idx = (i); \
5385 static_assert(idx <= 1 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5386 constexpr int start = 32 + 16 * (1 - idx); \
5387 constexpr int end = start + 15; \
5388 constexpr int shift_amount = idx * 16; \
5389 AtomicCmpExchangeHelper(addr, output, old_value, new_value, start, end, \
5390 shift_amount, -idx * 2, temp0, temp1); \
5391 }
5392#endif
5393
5394 Label two, done;
5395 tmll(addr, Operand(3));
5396 b(Condition(2), &two);
5397 ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(0);
5398 b(&done);
5399 bind(&two);
5400 ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(1);
5401 bind(&done);
5402}
5403
5404void MacroAssembler::AtomicExchangeHelper(Register addr, Register value,
5405 Register output, int start, int end,
5406 int shift_amount, int offset,
5407 Register scratch) {
5408 Label do_cs;
5409 LoadU32(output, MemOperand(addr, offset));
5410 bind(&do_cs);
5411 llgfr(scratch, output);
5412 RotateInsertSelectBits(scratch, value, Operand(start), Operand(end),
5413 Operand(shift_amount), false);
5414 csy(output, scratch, MemOperand(addr, offset));
5415 bne(&do_cs, Label::kNear);
5416 srl(output, Operand(shift_amount));
5417}
5418
5419void MacroAssembler::AtomicExchangeU8(Register addr, Register value,
5420 Register output, Register scratch) {
5421#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
5422#define ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(i) \
5423 { \
5424 constexpr int idx = (i); \
5425 static_assert(idx <= 3 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5426 constexpr int start = 32 + 8 * idx; \
5427 constexpr int end = start + 7; \
5428 constexpr int shift_amount = (3 - idx) * 8; \
5429 AtomicExchangeHelper(addr, value, output, start, end, shift_amount, -idx, \
5430 scratch); \
5431 }
5432#else
5433#define ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(i) \
5434 { \
5435 constexpr int idx = (i); \
5436 static_assert(idx <= 3 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5437 constexpr int start = 32 + 8 * (3 - idx); \
5438 constexpr int end = start + 7; \
5439 constexpr int shift_amount = idx * 8; \
5440 AtomicExchangeHelper(addr, value, output, start, end, shift_amount, -idx, \
5441 scratch); \
5442 }
5443#endif
5444 Label three, two, one, done;
5445 tmll(addr, Operand(3));
5446 b(Condition(1), &three);
5447 b(Condition(2), &two);
5448 b(Condition(4), &one);
5449
5450 // end with 0b00
5451 ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(0);
5452 b(&done);
5453
5454 // ending with 0b01
5455 bind(&one);
5456 ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(1);
5457 b(&done);
5458
5459 // ending with 0b10
5460 bind(&two);
5461 ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(2);
5462 b(&done);
5463
5464 // ending with 0b11
5465 bind(&three);
5466 ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(3);
5467
5468 bind(&done);
5469}
5470
5471void MacroAssembler::AtomicExchangeU16(Register addr, Register value,
5472 Register output, Register scratch) {
5473#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
5474#define ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(i) \
5475 { \
5476 constexpr int idx = (i); \
5477 static_assert(idx <= 1 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5478 constexpr int start = 32 + 16 * idx; \
5479 constexpr int end = start + 15; \
5480 constexpr int shift_amount = (1 - idx) * 16; \
5481 AtomicExchangeHelper(addr, value, output, start, end, shift_amount, \
5482 -idx * 2, scratch); \
5483 }
5484#else
5485#define ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(i) \
5486 { \
5487 constexpr int idx = (i); \
5488 static_assert(idx <= 1 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5489 constexpr int start = 32 + 16 * (1 - idx); \
5490 constexpr int end = start + 15; \
5491 constexpr int shift_amount = idx * 16; \
5492 AtomicExchangeHelper(addr, value, output, start, end, shift_amount, \
5493 -idx * 2, scratch); \
5494 }
5495#endif
5496 Label two, done;
5497 tmll(addr, Operand(3));
5498 b(Condition(2), &two);
5499
5500 // end with 0b00
5501 ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(0);
5502 b(&done);
5503
5504 // ending with 0b10
5505 bind(&two);
5506 ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(1);
5507
5508 bind(&done);
5509}

5825 void MacroAssembler::name(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1, \
5826 Simd128Register src2, Simd128Register scratch) { \
5827 mul_even(scratch, src1, src2, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
5828 Condition(mode)); \
5829 mul_odd(dst, src1, src2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(mode)); \

5842#define EMIT_SIMD_ALL_TRUE(name, mode) \
5843 void MacroAssembler::name(Register dst, Simd128Register src, \
5844 Register scratch1, Simd128Register scratch2) { \
5845 mov(scratch1, Operand(1)); \
5846 xgr(dst, dst); \
5847 vx(scratch2, scratch2, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
5848 Condition(2)); \

5850 vtm(scratch2, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0)); \

5852 }

5872void MacroAssembler::I64x2Mul(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
5873 Simd128Register src2, Register scratch1,
5874 Register scratch2, Register scratch3) {
5875 Register scratch_1 = scratch1;
5876 Register scratch_2 = scratch2;
5877 for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
5878 vlgv(scratch_1, src1, MemOperand(r0, i), Condition(3));
5879 vlgv(scratch_2, src2, MemOperand(r0, i), Condition(3));
5880 MulS64(scratch_1, scratch_2);
5881 scratch_1 = scratch2;
5882 scratch_2 = scratch3;
5883 }
5884 vlvgp(dst, scratch1, scratch2);
5885}

6046#define CONVERT_FLOAT_TO_INT32(convert, dst, src, scratch1, scratch2) \
6047 for (int index = 0; index < 4; index++) { \
6048 vlgv(scratch2, src, MemOperand(r0, index), Condition(2)); \
6049 MovIntToFloat(scratch1, scratch2); \
6050 convert(scratch2, scratch1, kRoundToZero); \
6051 vlvg(dst, scratch2, MemOperand(r0, index), Condition(2)); \
6052 }
6053void MacroAssembler::I32x4SConvertF32x4(Simd128Register dst,
6054 Simd128Register src,
6055 Simd128Register scratch1,
6056 Register scratch2) {
6057 // NaN to 0.
6058 vfce(scratch1, src, src, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(2));
6059 vn(dst, src, scratch1, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));
6060 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(VECTOR_ENHANCE_FACILITY_2)) {
6061 vcgd(dst, dst, Condition(5), Condition(0), Condition(2));
6062 } else {
6063 CONVERT_FLOAT_TO_INT32(ConvertFloat32ToInt32, dst, dst, scratch1, scratch2)
6064 }
6065}
6066
6067void MacroAssembler::I32x4UConvertF32x4(Simd128Register dst,
6068 Simd128Register src,
6069 Simd128Register scratch1,
6070 Register scratch2) {
6071 // vclgd or ConvertFloat32ToUnsignedInt32 will convert NaN to 0, negative to 0
6072 // automatically.
6073 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(VECTOR_ENHANCE_FACILITY_2)) {
6074 vclgd(dst, src, Condition(5), Condition(0), Condition(2));
6075 } else {
6076 CONVERT_FLOAT_TO_INT32(ConvertFloat32ToUnsignedInt32, dst, src, scratch1,
6077 scratch2)
6078 }
6079}
6080#undef CONVERT_FLOAT_TO_INT32
6081
6082#define CONVERT_INT32_TO_FLOAT(convert, dst, src, scratch1, scratch2) \
6083 for (int index = 0; index < 4; index++) { \
6084 vlgv(scratch2, src, MemOperand(r0, index), Condition(2)); \
6085 convert(scratch1, scratch2); \
6086 MovFloatToInt(scratch2, scratch1); \
6087 vlvg(dst, scratch2, MemOperand(r0, index), Condition(2)); \
6088 }
6089void MacroAssembler::F32x4SConvertI32x4(Simd128Register dst,
6090 Simd128Register src,
6091 Simd128Register scratch1,
6092 Register scratch2) {
6093 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(VECTOR_ENHANCE_FACILITY_2)) {
6094 vcdg(dst, src, Condition(4), Condition(0), Condition(2));
6095 } else {
6096 CONVERT_INT32_TO_FLOAT(ConvertIntToFloat, dst, src, scratch1, scratch2)
6097 }
6098}
6099void MacroAssembler::F32x4UConvertI32x4(Simd128Register dst,
6100 Simd128Register src,
6101 Simd128Register scratch1,
6102 Register scratch2) {
6103 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(VECTOR_ENHANCE_FACILITY_2)) {
6104 vcdlg(dst, src, Condition(4), Condition(0), Condition(2));
6105 } else {
6106 CONVERT_INT32_TO_FLOAT(ConvertUnsignedIntToFloat, dst, src, scratch1,
6107 scratch2)
6108 }
6109}
6110#undef CONVERT_INT32_TO_FLOAT

6124#define VECTOR_PACK_UNSIGNED(dst, src1, src2, scratch, mode) \
6125 vx(kDoubleRegZero, kDoubleRegZero, kDoubleRegZero, Condition(0), \
6126 Condition(0), Condition(mode)); \
6127 vmx(scratch, src1, kDoubleRegZero, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
6128 Condition(mode)); \
6129 vmx(dst, src2, kDoubleRegZero, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(mode));
6130void MacroAssembler::I16x8UConvertI32x4(Simd128Register dst,
6131 Simd128Register src1,
6132 Simd128Register src2,
6133 Simd128Register scratch) {
6134 // treat inputs as signed, and saturate to unsigned (negative to 0).
6135 VECTOR_PACK_UNSIGNED(dst, src1, src2, scratch, 2)
6136 vpkls(dst, dst, scratch, Condition(0), Condition(2));
6137}

6139void MacroAssembler::I8x16UConvertI16x8(Simd128Register dst,
6140 Simd128Register src1,
6141 Simd128Register src2,
6142 Simd128Register scratch) {
6143 // treat inputs as signed, and saturate to unsigned (negative to 0).
6144 VECTOR_PACK_UNSIGNED(dst, src1, src2, scratch, 1)
6145 vpkls(dst, dst, scratch, Condition(0), Condition(1));
6146}
6147#undef VECTOR_PACK_UNSIGNED

6149#define BINOP_EXTRACT(dst, src1, src2, scratch1, scratch2, op, extract_high, \
6150 extract_low, mode) \
6151 DCHECK(dst != scratch1 && dst != scratch2); \
6152 DCHECK(dst != src1 && dst != src2); \
6153 extract_high(scratch1, src1, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(mode)); \
6154 extract_high(scratch2, src2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(mode)); \
6155 op(dst, scratch1, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
6156 Condition(mode + 1)); \
6157 extract_low(scratch1, src1, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(mode)); \
6158 extract_low(scratch2, src2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(mode)); \
6159 op(scratch1, scratch1, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
6160 Condition(mode + 1));
6161void MacroAssembler::I16x8AddSatS(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
6162 Simd128Register src2,
6163 Simd128Register scratch1,
6164 Simd128Register scratch2) {
6165 BINOP_EXTRACT(dst, src1, src2, scratch1, scratch2, va, vuph, vupl, 1)
6166 vpks(dst, dst, scratch1, Condition(0), Condition(2));
6167}

6172 Simd128Register scratch2) {

6174 vpks(dst, dst, scratch1, Condition(0), Condition(2));
6175}

6177void MacroAssembler::I16x8AddSatU(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
6178 Simd128Register src2,
6179 Simd128Register scratch1,

6184
6185void MacroAssembler::I16x8SubSatU(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
6186 Simd128Register src2,
6187 Simd128Register scratch1,
6188 Simd128Register scratch2) {
6189 BINOP_EXTRACT(dst, src1, src2, scratch1, scratch2, vs, vuplh, vupll, 1)
6190 // negative intermediate values to 0.
6191 vx(kDoubleRegZero, kDoubleRegZero, kDoubleRegZero, Condition(0), Condition(0),
6192 Condition(0));
6193 vmx(dst, kDoubleRegZero, dst, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(2));
6194 vmx(scratch1, kDoubleRegZero, scratch1, Condition(0), Condition(0),
6195 Condition(2));
6196 vpkls(dst, dst, scratch1, Condition(0), Condition(2));
6197}

6205}

6207void MacroAssembler::I8x16SubSatS(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
6208 Simd128Register src2,
6209 Simd128Register scratch1,
6210 Simd128Register scratch2) {
6211 BINOP_EXTRACT(dst, src1, src2, scratch1, scratch2, vs, vuph, vupl, 0)
6212 vpks(dst, dst, scratch1, Condition(0), Condition(1));
6213}

6223void MacroAssembler::I8x16SubSatU(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
6224 Simd128Register src2,
6225 Simd128Register scratch1,
6226 Simd128Register scratch2) {

6228 // negative intermediate values to 0.

6230 Condition(0));

6232 vmx(scratch1, kDoubleRegZero, scratch1, Condition(0), Condition(0),
6233 Condition(1));
6234 vpkls(dst, dst, scratch1, Condition(0), Condition(1));
6235}

6238void MacroAssembler::F64x2PromoteLowF32x4(Simd128Register dst,
6239 Simd128Register src,
6240 Simd128Register scratch1,
6241 Register scratch2, Register scratch3,
6242 Register scratch4) {
6243 Register holder = scratch3;
6244 for (int index = 0; index < 2; ++index) {
6245 vlgv(scratch2, src, MemOperand(scratch2, index + 2), Condition(2));
6246 MovIntToFloat(scratch1, scratch2);
6247 ldebr(scratch1, scratch1);
6248 MovDoubleToInt64(holder, scratch1);
6249 holder = scratch4;
6250 }
6251 vlvgp(dst, scratch3, scratch4);
6252}

6254void MacroAssembler::F32x4DemoteF64x2Zero(Simd128Register dst,
6255 Simd128Register src,
6256 Simd128Register scratch1,
6257 Register scratch2, Register scratch3,
6258 Register scratch4) {
6259 Register holder = scratch3;
6260 for (int index = 0; index < 2; ++index) {
6261 vlgv(scratch2, src, MemOperand(r0, index), Condition(3));
6262 MovInt64ToDouble(scratch1, scratch2);
6263 ledbr(scratch1, scratch1);
6264 MovFloatToInt(holder, scratch1);
6265 holder = scratch4;
6266 }
6267 vx(dst, dst, dst, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(2));
6268 vlvg(dst, scratch3, MemOperand(r0, 2), Condition(2));
6269 vlvg(dst, scratch4, MemOperand(r0, 3), Condition(2));
6270}

6272#define EXT_ADD_PAIRWISE(dst, src, scratch1, scratch2, lane_size, mul_even, \
6273 mul_odd) \
6274 CHECK_NE(src, scratch2); \
6275 vrepi(scratch2, Operand(1), Condition(lane_size)); \
6276 mul_even(scratch1, src, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
6277 Condition(lane_size)); \
6278 mul_odd(scratch2, src, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
6279 Condition(lane_size)); \
6280 va(dst, scratch1, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
6281 Condition(lane_size + 1));

6343
6344void MacroAssembler::I8x16Swizzle(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
6345 Simd128Register src2, Register scratch1,
6346 Register scratch2, Simd128Register scratch3) {
6347 DCHECK(!AreAliased(src1, src2, scratch3));
6348 // Saturate the indices to 5 bits. Input indices more than 31 should
6349 // return 0.
6350 vrepi(scratch3, Operand(31), Condition(0));
6351 vmnl(scratch3, src2, scratch3, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));
6352 // Input needs to be reversed.
6353 vlgv(scratch1, src1, MemOperand(r0, 0), Condition(3));
6354 vlgv(scratch2, src1, MemOperand(r0, 1), Condition(3));
6355 lrvgr(scratch1, scratch1);
6356 lrvgr(scratch2, scratch2);
6357 vlvgp(dst, scratch2, scratch1);
6358 vx(kDoubleRegZero, kDoubleRegZero, kDoubleRegZero, Condition(0), Condition(0),
6359 Condition(0));
6360 vperm(dst, dst, kDoubleRegZero, scratch3, Condition(0), Condition(0));
6361}

6363void MacroAssembler::I8x16Shuffle(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
6364 Simd128Register src2, uint64_t high,
6365 uint64_t low, Register scratch1,
6366 Register scratch2, Simd128Register scratch3) {
6367 mov(scratch1, Operand(low));
6368 mov(scratch2, Operand(high));
6369 vlvgp(scratch3, scratch2, scratch1);
6370 vperm(dst, src1, src2, scratch3, Condition(0), Condition(0));
6371}

6381void MacroAssembler::I32x4DotI8x16AddS(
6382 Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1, Simd128Register src2,
6383 Simd128Register src3, Simd128Register scratch1, Simd128Register scratch2) {
6384 DCHECK_NE(dst, src3);
6385 // I8 -> I16.
6386 vme(scratch1, src1, src2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));
6387 vmo(dst, src1, src2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));
6388 va(dst, scratch1, dst, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(1));
6389 // I16 -> I32.
6390 vrepi(scratch2, Operand(1), Condition(1));
6391 vme(scratch1, dst, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(1));
6392 vmo(dst, dst, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(1));
6393 va(dst, scratch1, dst, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(2));
6394 // Add src3.
6395 va(dst, dst, src3, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(2));
6396}

6404}

6406#define Q15_MUL_ROAUND(accumulator, src1, src2, const_val, scratch, unpack) \
6407 unpack(scratch, src1, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(1)); \
6408 unpack(accumulator, src2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(1)); \
6409 vml(accumulator, scratch, accumulator, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
6410 Condition(2)); \
6411 va(accumulator, accumulator, const_val, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
6412 Condition(2)); \
6413 vrepi(scratch, Operand(15), Condition(2)); \
6414 vesrav(accumulator, accumulator, scratch, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
6415 Condition(2));
6416void MacroAssembler::I16x8Q15MulRSatS(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
6417 Simd128Register src2,
6418 Simd128Register scratch1,
6419 Simd128Register scratch2,
6420 Simd128Register scratch3) {
6421 DCHECK(!AreAliased(src1, src2, scratch1, scratch2, scratch3));
6422 vrepi(scratch1, Operand(0x4000), Condition(2));
6423 Q15_MUL_ROAUND(scratch2, src1, src2, scratch1, scratch3, vupl)
6424 Q15_MUL_ROAUND(dst, src1, src2, scratch1, scratch3, vuph)
6425 vpks(dst, dst, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(2));
6426}

6429// Vector LE Load and Transform instructions.
6430#ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
6431#define IS_BIG_ENDIAN true
6432#else
6433#define IS_BIG_ENDIAN false
6434#endif
6435
6436#define CAN_LOAD_STORE_REVERSE \
6437 IS_BIG_ENDIAN&& CpuFeatures::IsSupported(VECTOR_ENHANCE_FACILITY_2)
6438
6439#define LOAD_SPLAT_LIST(V) \
6440 V(64x2, vlbrrep, LoadU64LE, 3) \
6441 V(32x4, vlbrrep, LoadU32LE, 2) \
6442 V(16x8, vlbrrep, LoadU16LE, 1) \
6443 V(8x16, vlrep, LoadU8, 0)
6444
6445#define LOAD_SPLAT(name, vector_instr, scalar_instr, condition) \
6446 void MacroAssembler::LoadAndSplat##name##LE( \
6447 Simd128Register dst, const MemOperand& mem, Register scratch) { \
6448 if (CAN_LOAD_STORE_REVERSE && is_uint12(mem.offset())) { \
6449 vector_instr(dst, mem, Condition(condition)); \
6450 return; \
6451 } \
6452 scalar_instr(scratch, mem); \
6453 vlvg(dst, scratch, MemOperand(r0, 0), Condition(condition)); \
6454 vrep(dst, dst, Operand(0), Condition(condition)); \
6455 }
6456LOAD_SPLAT_LIST(LOAD_SPLAT)
6457#undef LOAD_SPLAT
6458#undef LOAD_SPLAT_LIST
6459
6460#define LOAD_EXTEND_LIST(V) \
6461 V(32x2U, vuplh, 2) \
6462 V(32x2S, vuph, 2) \
6463 V(16x4U, vuplh, 1) \
6464 V(16x4S, vuph, 1) \
6465 V(8x8U, vuplh, 0) \
6466 V(8x8S, vuph, 0)
6467
6468#define LOAD_EXTEND(name, unpack_instr, condition) \
6469 void MacroAssembler::LoadAndExtend##name##LE( \
6470 Simd128Register dst, const MemOperand& mem, Register scratch) { \
6471 if (CAN_LOAD_STORE_REVERSE && is_uint12(mem.offset())) { \
6472 vlebrg(dst, mem, Condition(0)); \
6473 } else { \
6474 LoadU64LE(scratch, mem); \
6475 vlvg(dst, scratch, MemOperand(r0, 0), Condition(3)); \
6476 } \
6477 unpack_instr(dst, dst, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(condition)); \
6478 }
6479LOAD_EXTEND_LIST(LOAD_EXTEND)
6480#undef LOAD_EXTEND
6481#undef LOAD_EXTEND

6483void MacroAssembler::LoadV32ZeroLE(Simd128Register dst, const MemOperand& mem,
6484 Register scratch) {
6485 vx(dst, dst, dst, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));
6486 if (CAN_LOAD_STORE_REVERSE && is_uint12(mem.offset())) {
6487 vlebrf(dst, mem, Condition(3));
6488 return;
6489 }
6490 LoadU32LE(scratch, mem);
6491 vlvg(dst, scratch, MemOperand(r0, 3), Condition(2));
6492}
6493
6494void MacroAssembler::LoadV64ZeroLE(Simd128Register dst, const MemOperand& mem,
6495 Register scratch) {
6496 vx(dst, dst, dst, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));
6497 if (CAN_LOAD_STORE_REVERSE && is_uint12(mem.offset())) {
6498 vlebrg(dst, mem, Condition(1));
6499 return;
6500 }
6501 LoadU64LE(scratch, mem);
6502 vlvg(dst, scratch, MemOperand(r0, 1), Condition(3));
6503}
