6505#define LOAD_LANE_LIST(V) \
6506 V(64, vlebrg, LoadU64LE, 3) \
6507 V(32, vlebrf, LoadU32LE, 2) \
6508 V(16, vlebrh, LoadU16LE, 1) \
6509 V(8, vleb, LoadU8, 0)
6510
6511#define LOAD_LANE(name, vector_instr, scalar_instr, condition) \
6512 void MacroAssembler::LoadLane##name##LE(Simd128Register dst, \
6513 const MemOperand& mem, int lane, \
6514 Register scratch) { \
6515 if (CAN_LOAD_STORE_REVERSE && is_uint12(mem.offset())) { \
6516 vector_instr(dst, mem, Condition(lane)); \
6517 return; \
6518 } \
6519 scalar_instr(scratch, mem); \
6520 vlvg(dst, scratch, MemOperand(r0, lane), Condition(condition)); \
6521 }
6522LOAD_LANE_LIST(LOAD_LANE)
6523#undef LOAD_LANE
6524#undef LOAD_LANE_LIST
6525
6526#define STORE_LANE_LIST(V) \
6527 V(64, vstebrg, StoreU64LE, 3) \
6528 V(32, vstebrf, StoreU32LE, 2) \
6529 V(16, vstebrh, StoreU16LE, 1) \
6530 V(8, vsteb, StoreU8, 0)
6531
6532#define STORE_LANE(name, vector_instr, scalar_instr, condition) \
6533 void MacroAssembler::StoreLane##name##LE(Simd128Register src, \
6534 const MemOperand& mem, int lane, \
6535 Register scratch) { \
6536 if (CAN_LOAD_STORE_REVERSE && is_uint12(mem.offset())) { \
6537 vector_instr(src, mem, Condition(lane)); \
6538 return; \
6539 } \
6540 vlgv(scratch, src, MemOperand(r0, lane), Condition(condition)); \
6541 scalar_instr(scratch, mem); \
6542 }
6543STORE_LANE_LIST(STORE_LANE)
6544#undef STORE_LANE
6545#undef STORE_LANE_LIST
6546#undef CAN_LOAD_STORE_REVERSE
6547#undef IS_BIG_ENDIAN
6548
6549void MacroAssembler::LoadStackLimit(Register destination, StackLimitKind kind) {
6550 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6551 DCHECK(root_array_available());
6552 intptr_t offset = kind == StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit
6553 ? IsolateData::real_jslimit_offset()
6554 : IsolateData::jslimit_offset();
6555 CHECK(is_int32(offset));
6556 LoadU64(destination, MemOperand(kRootRegister, offset));
6557}
6558
6559void MacroAssembler::Switch(Register scratch, Register value,
6560 int case_value_base, Label** labels,
6561 int num_labels) {
6562 Label fallthrough, jump_table;
6563 if (case_value_base != 0) {
6564 SubS64(value, value, Operand(case_value_base));
6565 }
6566 CmpU64(value, Operand(num_labels));
6567 bge(&fallthrough);
6568
6569 int entry_size_log2 = 3;
6570 ShiftLeftU32(value, value, Operand(entry_size_log2));
6571 larl(r1, &jump_table);
6572 lay(r1, MemOperand(value, r1));
6573 b(r1);
6574
6575 bind(&jump_table);
6576 for (int i = 0; i < num_labels; ++i) {
6577 b(labels[i]);
6578 dh(0);
6579 }
6580 bind(&fallthrough);
6581}
6582
6583void MacroAssembler::JumpIfCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(
6584 Register code, Register scratch, Label* if_marked_for_deoptimization) {
6585 TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(code, scratch);
6586 bne(if_marked_for_deoptimization);
6587}
6588
6589void MacroAssembler::JumpIfCodeIsTurbofanned(Register code, Register scratch,
6590 Label* if_turbofanned) {
6591 LoadU32(scratch, FieldMemOperand(code, Code::kFlagsOffset));
6592 TestBit(scratch, Code::kIsTurbofannedBit, scratch);
6593 bne(if_turbofanned);
6594}
6595
6596void MacroAssembler::TryLoadOptimizedOsrCode(Register scratch_and_result,
6597 CodeKind min_opt_level,
6598 Register feedback_vector,
6599 FeedbackSlot slot,
6600 Label* on_result,
6601 Label::Distance) {
6602 Label fallthrough, clear_slot;
6603 LoadTaggedField(
6604 scratch_and_result,
6605 FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
6606 FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())));
6607 LoadWeakValue(scratch_and_result, scratch_and_result, &fallthrough);
6608
6609 // Is it marked_for_deoptimization? If yes, clear the slot.
6610 {
6611 // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
6612 LoadTaggedField(
6613 scratch_and_result,
6614 FieldMemOperand(scratch_and_result, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
6615
6616 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6617 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
6618 JumpIfCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(scratch_and_result, temp, &clear_slot);
6619 if (min_opt_level == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS) {
6620 JumpIfCodeIsTurbofanned(scratch_and_result, temp, on_result);
6621 b(&fallthrough);
6622 } else {
6623 b(on_result);
6624 }
6625 }
6626
6627 bind(&clear_slot);
6628 mov(scratch_and_result, ClearedValue());
6629 StoreTaggedField(
6630 scratch_and_result,
6631 FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
6632 FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())));
6633
6634 bind(&fallthrough);
6635 mov(scratch_and_result, Operand::Zero());
6636}
6637
6638// Calls an API function. Allocates HandleScope, extracts returned value
6639// from handle and propagates exceptions. Clobbers C argument registers
6640// and C caller-saved registers. Restores context. On return removes
6641// (*argc_operand + slots_to_drop_on_return) * kSystemPointerSize
6642// (GCed, includes the call JS arguments space and the additional space
6643// allocated for the fast call).
6644void CallApiFunctionAndReturn(MacroAssembler* masm, bool with_profiling,
6645 Register function_address,
6646 ExternalReference thunk_ref, Register thunk_arg,
6647 int slots_to_drop_on_return,
6648 MemOperand* argc_operand,
6649 MemOperand return_value_operand) {
6650 using ER = ExternalReference;
6651
6652 Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
6653 MemOperand next_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6654 ER::handle_scope_next_address(isolate), no_reg);
6655 MemOperand limit_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6656 ER::handle_scope_limit_address(isolate), no_reg);
6657 MemOperand level_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6658 ER::handle_scope_level_address(isolate), no_reg);
6659
6660 Register return_value = r2;
6661#if V8_OS_ZOS
6662 Register scratch = r6;
6663#else
6664 Register scratch = ip;
6665#endif
6666 Register scratch2 = r1;
6667
6668 // Allocate HandleScope in callee-saved registers.
6669 // We will need to restore the HandleScope after the call to the API function,
6670 // by allocating it in callee-saved registers it'll be preserved by C code.
6671#if V8_OS_ZOS
6672 Register prev_next_address_reg = r14;
6673#else
6674 Register prev_next_address_reg = r6;
6675#endif
6676 Register prev_limit_reg = r7;
6677 Register prev_level_reg = r8;
6678
6679 // C arguments (kCArgRegs[0/1]) are expected to be initialized outside, so
6680 // this function must not corrupt them (return_value overlaps with
6681 // kCArgRegs[0] but that's ok because we start using it only after the C
6682 // call).
6683 DCHECK(!AreAliased(kCArgRegs[0], kCArgRegs[1], // C args
6684 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6685 // function_address and thunk_arg might overlap but this function must not
6686 // corrupted them until the call is made (i.e. overlap with return_value is
6687 // fine).
6688 DCHECK(!AreAliased(function_address, // incoming parameters
6689 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6690 DCHECK(!AreAliased(thunk_arg, // incoming parameters
6691 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6692 {
6693 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
6694 "Allocate HandleScope in callee-save registers.");
6695 __ LoadU64(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
6696 __ LoadU64(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
6697 __ LoadU32(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
6698 __ AddS64(scratch, prev_level_reg, Operand(1));
6699 __ StoreU32(scratch, level_mem_op);
6700 }
6701
6702 Label profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, done_api_call;
6703 if (with_profiling) {
6704 __ RecordComment("Check if profiler or side effects check is enabled");
6705 __ LoadU8(scratch,
6706 __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kExecutionMode));
6707 __ CmpS64(scratch, Operand::Zero());
6708 __ bne(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, Label::kNear);
6709#ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6710 __ RecordComment("Check if RCS is enabled");
6711 __ Move(scratch, ER::address_of_runtime_stats_flag());
6712 __ LoadU32(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
6713 __ CmpS64(scratch, Operand::Zero());
6714 __ bne(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, Label::kNear);
6715#endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6716 }
6717
6718 __ RecordComment("Call the api function directly.");
6719#if V8_OS_ZOS
6720 __ mov(scratch, function_address);
6721 __ zosStoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address, scratch);
6722#else
6723 __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address);
6724#endif
6725 __ bind(&done_api_call);
6726
6727 Label propagate_exception;
6728 Label delete_allocated_handles;
6729 Label leave_exit_frame;
6730
6731 __ RecordComment("Load the value from ReturnValue");
6732 __ LoadU64(r2, return_value_operand);
6733
6734 {
6735 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
6736 masm,
6737 "No more valid handles (the result handle was the last one)."
6738 "Restore previous handle scope.");
6739 __ StoreU64(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
6740 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6741 __ LoadU32(scratch, level_mem_op);
6742 __ SubS64(scratch, Operand(1));
6743 __ CmpS64(scratch, prev_level_reg);
6744 __ Check(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedLevelAfterReturnFromApiCall);
6745 }
6746 __ StoreU32(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
6747 __ CmpS64(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
6748 __ bne(&delete_allocated_handles, Label::kNear);
6749 }
6750
6751 __ RecordComment("Leave the API exit frame.");
6752 __ bind(&leave_exit_frame);
6753 Register argc_reg = prev_limit_reg;
6754 if (argc_operand != nullptr) {
6755 // Load the number of stack slots to drop before LeaveExitFrame modifies sp.
6756 __ LoadU64(argc_reg, *argc_operand);
6757 }
6758 __ LeaveExitFrame(scratch);
6759
6760 // Check if the function scheduled an exception.
6761 {
6762 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
6763 "Check if the function scheduled an exception.");
6764 __ LoadU64(scratch2, __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6765 ER::exception_address(isolate), no_reg));
6766 __ CompareRoot(scratch2, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
6767 __ bne(&propagate_exception, Label::kNear);
6768 }
6769
6770 __ AssertJSAny(return_value, scratch, scratch2,
6771 AbortReason::kAPICallReturnedInvalidObject);
6772
6773 if (argc_operand == nullptr) {
6774 DCHECK_NE(slots_to_drop_on_return, 0);
6775 __ AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
6776
6777 } else {
6778 // {argc_operand} was loaded into {argc_reg} above.
6779 __ AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
6780 __ ShiftLeftU64(r0, argc_reg, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
6781 __ AddS64(sp, sp, r0);
6782 }
6783
6784 __ b(r14);
6785
6786 if (with_profiling) {
6787 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Call the api function via thunk wrapper.");
6788 __ bind(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
6789 // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback function.
6790 if (thunk_arg.is_valid()) {
6791 MemOperand thunk_arg_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6792 IsolateFieldId::kApiCallbackThunkArgument);
6793 __ StoreU64(thunk_arg, thunk_arg_mem_op);
6794 }
6795 __ Move(scratch, thunk_ref);
6796#if V8_OS_ZOS
6797 __ zosStoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address, scratch);
6798#else
6799 __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(scratch);
6800#endif
6801 __ b(&done_api_call);
6802 }
6803
6804 __ RecordComment("An exception was thrown. Propagate it.");
6805 __ bind(&propagate_exception);
6806 __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kPropagateException);
6807
6808 // HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.
6809 {
6810 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
6811 masm, "HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.");
6812 __ bind(&delete_allocated_handles);
6813 __ StoreU64(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
6814 // Save the return value in a callee-save register.
6815 Register saved_result = prev_limit_reg;
6816 __ mov(saved_result, return_value);
6817 __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, scratch);
6818 __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
6819 __ CallCFunction(ER::delete_handle_scope_extensions(), 1);
6820 __ mov(return_value, saved_result);
6821 __ b(&leave_exit_frame, Label::kNear);
6822 }
6823}
6824
6825} // namespace internal
6826} // namespace v8
6827
6828#undef __
6829
6830#endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_S390X

friend Zone
